WEBVTT

00:09.103 --> 00:12.034
[soft holiday music]

00:12.103 --> 00:15.103
[cars honking]

00:21.896 --> 00:24.931
[indistinct chatter]

00:30.137 --> 00:32.310
[Michael Bublé's
"Cold December Night"]

00:32.378 --> 00:37.724
- ♪ But now I know what
my heart wants you to bring ♪

00:37.793 --> 00:41.137
♪ So please just fall in love
with me ♪

00:41.206 --> 00:44.896
♪ This Christmas,
there's nothing else ♪

00:44.965 --> 00:48.482
- Well, here you are, sir.
- Oh, thank you.

00:48.551 --> 00:51.241
- Here you go.
My lovely wife.

00:51.310 --> 00:53.413
Here.
You take this.

00:53.482 --> 00:55.689
And...

00:55.758 --> 00:57.827
cheers to your fifth year here.

00:57.896 --> 00:59.517
[chuckles]
- I will drink to that.

00:59.586 --> 01:01.000
Cheers.
- Cheers.

01:01.068 --> 01:03.862
So Wyatt, any big plans
for the holidays?

01:03.931 --> 01:06.310
Oh, are you finally gonna meet
Lindsey's parents?

01:06.379 --> 01:09.482
- Oh, um, Lindsey and I
broke up in October.

01:09.551 --> 01:11.448
- Oh.
Hugh, you didn't tell me that.

01:11.517 --> 01:13.172
- Oh, I didn't know.

01:13.241 --> 01:16.137
- Wyatt, I am so sorry.
- Mm.

01:16.206 --> 01:17.620
- What did you expect him
to do?

01:17.689 --> 01:19.517
They were getting too serious.
- What, is that true?

01:19.586 --> 01:21.310
Is that why
the two of you broke up?

01:21.379 --> 01:22.724
- Maybe?

01:22.793 --> 01:25.033
Or maybe it was the
nonstop trips to the Cape.

01:25.103 --> 01:27.000
Or maybe it was
the five-star restaurants

01:27.068 --> 01:28.551
that we had to go to
every other night.

01:28.620 --> 01:30.896
Honestly, I just wanted
a nice, quiet weekend at home

01:30.965 --> 01:32.482
once in a while
without all the fuss.

01:32.551 --> 01:34.241
- And now you have it.
[chuckles]

01:34.310 --> 01:36.000
- But what are you
gonna do for Christmas?

01:36.068 --> 01:37.378
Why don't you come over
to the house?

01:37.448 --> 01:38.965
- That's very, very sweet
of you to offer,

01:39.033 --> 01:41.344
but I think I might be
going home this year.

01:41.413 --> 01:43.551
- Your mother must be thrilled
to have you coming home.

01:43.620 --> 01:47.344
- Honestly, I'm--I'm not
too excited about going home.

01:47.413 --> 01:50.689
I'm still kind of on the fence.
- Wait, is everything okay?

01:50.758 --> 01:53.344
- Um...I don't know.

01:53.413 --> 01:55.551
My mom seems to be having
a hard time lately,

01:55.620 --> 01:57.103
especially this year,

01:57.172 --> 02:00.413
and well, it's been a while
since my father passed away,

02:00.482 --> 02:02.379
so I really don't know
what's going on with her.

02:02.448 --> 02:03.655
- Mm-hmm.
- Well...

02:03.724 --> 02:05.586
I hope you take your laptop
with you.

02:05.655 --> 02:07.379
Get some work done
while you're there.

02:07.448 --> 02:08.896
- Don't you worry.

02:08.965 --> 02:10.723
I'm gonna bring all my work
with me.

02:10.793 --> 02:12.723
I just thought probably
the best time to do this

02:12.793 --> 02:14.586
was around the holidays
while I can.

02:14.655 --> 02:17.000
With your blessing,
of course, sir.

02:17.068 --> 02:19.931
- Of course
you have his blessing.

02:20.000 --> 02:21.206
- Truly, I wouldn't go
if I thought

02:21.275 --> 02:22.724
there was any other choice.

02:22.793 --> 02:25.482
- Beautiful horse ranch
in a snowy Colorado mountain?

02:25.551 --> 02:28.724
Warm cider by the fire?
Ooh, yeah, that sounds awful.

02:28.793 --> 02:30.896
- I know,
beautiful horse ranch,

02:30.965 --> 02:33.103
or dried-up wishing well
these days.

02:33.172 --> 02:34.379
We shall see.

02:34.448 --> 02:36.000
And my mother would throw
every single penny

02:36.067 --> 02:38.206
of her retirement into
that wishing well if I let her.

02:38.275 --> 02:41.758
- Oh, well, be a good son
and go help her out then.

02:41.827 --> 02:43.413
Come on, Mr. Clancy.

02:43.482 --> 02:45.413
Come spin me around
the dance floor.

02:45.482 --> 02:48.275
Au revoir!
[chuckles]

02:48.344 --> 02:49.862
[champagne bottle pops]

02:49.930 --> 02:52.172
- [sighs]

02:58.103 --> 03:01.103
[sentimental music]

03:01.172 --> 03:08.172
♪ ♪

03:16.689 --> 03:17.896
- [sighs]

03:22.379 --> 03:24.551
Good morning.

03:24.620 --> 03:26.034
- Morning.

03:26.103 --> 03:29.103
- I've come bearing tea
and good news.

03:29.172 --> 03:31.172
- Santa's getting us
a new sleigh.

03:31.241 --> 03:35.689
- No, Wyatt's coming home
for Christmas.

03:35.758 --> 03:37.896
- That's wonderful.
When does he get in?

03:37.965 --> 03:41.862
- As far as I know,
he'll be here tomorrow.

03:41.930 --> 03:45.137
- Wow, this is the
first Christmas he's been back

03:45.206 --> 03:46.344
in, how long?

03:46.413 --> 03:48.793
Like four or five years?
- That's right.

03:48.862 --> 03:51.172
I went to see him
two Christmases ago,

03:51.241 --> 03:53.000
but that's it.

03:53.067 --> 03:55.413
You know, I was really
starting to wonder

03:55.482 --> 03:57.137
if he was ever gonna come home.

03:57.206 --> 03:59.034
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

03:59.103 --> 04:02.068
- Heath, have you even
met Wyatt yet?

04:02.137 --> 04:04.931
- Nope, no, I've only been here
on the ranch, what?

04:05.000 --> 04:06.344
Three years?

04:06.413 --> 04:10.241
But I do know that you dated
Deb's successful son

04:10.310 --> 04:11.931
back in high school,
didn't you?

04:12.000 --> 04:14.068
- Yeah, yeah,
I dated Wyatt in high school

04:14.137 --> 04:15.758
till junior year.

04:15.827 --> 04:17.481
But it feels like
a lifetime ago.

04:17.551 --> 04:18.896
- It sure does.

04:18.964 --> 04:21.206
Boy, it's gonna be nice
to have him home.

04:21.274 --> 04:23.827
- That is if we accept
his apology

04:23.896 --> 04:25.654
upon return, huh, Dash?

04:25.724 --> 04:27.206
- Wyatt knows Dash?
- He should.

04:27.274 --> 04:29.241
It's his horse.
- [laughs]

04:29.310 --> 04:31.862
Was his horse
before he took off

04:31.931 --> 04:33.793
and left us all here
high and dry.

04:33.862 --> 04:35.758
I mean, the last few times
Wyatt came back,

04:35.827 --> 04:37.896
he wouldn't even
come see Dasher.

04:37.965 --> 04:40.034
He basically stayed
at the hotel in town.

04:40.103 --> 04:41.103
That's my tea.

04:41.172 --> 04:43.827
- Wyatt can be
a bit of a loner.

04:43.896 --> 04:45.310
- Not when we were growing up,
he wasn't.

04:45.379 --> 04:47.862
- Well,
you two were inseparable.

04:47.931 --> 04:49.517
- Don't you think
Sam might be jealous

04:49.586 --> 04:53.103
with Wyatt being home and him
still out of the country?

04:55.586 --> 04:58.103
- Somehow, I don't think so.
- [chuckles]

04:58.172 --> 05:00.000
- He could help fix
the carriage sled, though.

05:00.068 --> 05:02.206
He knows it well.
- Oh, no!

05:02.275 --> 05:04.793
You couldn't fix it?
- No, it's holding on for now.

05:04.862 --> 05:06.517
But we should be back
in business tomorrow.

05:06.586 --> 05:08.689
If you want, I'll blast it
to the mailing list.

05:08.758 --> 05:09.827
- Okay.
Thanks, hon.

05:09.896 --> 05:11.793
- That's what
I'm here for, Deb.

05:11.862 --> 05:15.034
Okay, Snow.
[horse neighs]

05:15.103 --> 05:17.241
Let's get out there and see...
- Uh...

05:17.310 --> 05:18.758
Heath doesn't know about Wyatt?

05:18.827 --> 05:20.758
- Well,
what was I supposed to say?

05:20.827 --> 05:24.413
"By the way, my son's gay too.
You're two of a kind"?

05:24.482 --> 05:26.586
- No, but does Wyatt know
about Heath?

05:26.655 --> 05:29.931
- Oh, gosh, Wyatt only calls
to make sure I'm exercising

05:30.000 --> 05:33.862
and taking those stupid
supplements he sends me.

05:33.931 --> 05:38.000
Honestly, I've never had a
chance to tell him about Heath.

05:38.068 --> 05:40.068
- Well, at least he's still
looking out for you.

05:40.137 --> 05:42.275
- I know.
It's so sweet.

05:42.344 --> 05:44.931
My baby's taking care of me.
- Hmm.

05:45.000 --> 05:48.310
- Here.
To stay warm.

05:48.379 --> 05:52.413
All right, next stop,
Santa's workshop.

05:52.482 --> 05:53.551
[kids cheer]

05:53.620 --> 06:00.103
♪ ♪

06:00.172 --> 06:03.068
The stables back there
are for the reindeer,

06:03.137 --> 06:06.724
not the horses,
and this is Santa's workshop.

06:13.896 --> 06:17.103
- ♪ Won't you take me home
for Christmas? ♪

06:17.172 --> 06:19.275
♪ Show me around your town ♪

06:19.344 --> 06:21.827
♪ Take me where
you used to watch ♪

06:21.896 --> 06:24.551
♪ The snow come down ♪

06:24.620 --> 06:29.724
♪ All of your traditions,
I wanna know them all ♪

06:29.793 --> 06:33.310
♪ You'll check every box
off of my list ♪

06:33.379 --> 06:36.827
♪ If you take me home
for Christmas ♪

06:36.896 --> 06:39.137
- ♪ Take me home ♪

06:39.206 --> 06:41.724
♪ Take me home ♪

06:41.793 --> 06:43.827
♪ Take me home ♪

06:43.896 --> 06:46.896
♪ ♪

06:46.965 --> 06:49.965
- [grunts]

06:50.034 --> 06:53.034
[exhales]

06:53.103 --> 06:54.482
[birds chirping]

06:54.551 --> 06:56.172
- Hey!
Oh!

06:56.241 --> 06:58.689
- Oh, hey, Mom.
- Aww.

06:58.758 --> 07:01.344
- Good to see you too.
- What has it been?

07:01.413 --> 07:02.689
Two years?
- Oh.

07:02.758 --> 07:04.896
We just FaceTimed
two months ago.

07:04.965 --> 07:07.068
- It's not the same
as hugging your kid.

07:07.137 --> 07:08.586
Maybe you'll have kids
of your own one day

07:08.655 --> 07:10.448
and you'll understand.

07:10.517 --> 07:13.137
So how are things in Manhattan?
- Good, good.

07:13.206 --> 07:15.655
Everything's good.
- And things with Lindsey?

07:15.724 --> 07:17.413
- We broke up.
- Oh, no.

07:17.482 --> 07:18.758
You must've broken his heart.

07:18.827 --> 07:20.275
From what you said,
he was crazy about you.

07:20.344 --> 07:22.551
- Well, I'm sure he's crazy
about someone else by now.

07:22.620 --> 07:24.379
Kid's got a lot
of growing up to do.

07:24.448 --> 07:26.724
What about you?
Any irons in the fire?

07:26.793 --> 07:28.931
- Oh, yes, just
a revolving door of men.

07:29.000 --> 07:31.379
- [laughs] What about Carlos?
You still seeing him?

07:31.448 --> 07:33.172
- Carlos?
No, what?

07:33.241 --> 07:35.379
You know Carlos retired
three years ago?

07:35.448 --> 07:38.448
- Okay, that's not exactly
what I asked, but...

07:38.517 --> 07:41.758
- Oh, honey, it's just
so nice to have you home.

07:41.827 --> 07:43.620
- Oh, sh--
- [laughs]

07:43.689 --> 07:45.827
- All right.
- Uh-oh.

07:45.896 --> 07:47.965
- Not much has changed
around here.

07:48.034 --> 07:51.758
It still smells like
horse crap and pine cones.

07:51.827 --> 07:54.068
Who's that over
by the carriage?

07:54.137 --> 07:55.551
- Oh, that's Heath.

07:55.620 --> 07:57.517
He's been working on the ranch
for a few years.

07:57.586 --> 07:58.896
He and Blake
are thick as thieves.

07:58.965 --> 08:01.172
- Oh, really?
Traitor.

08:01.241 --> 08:03.137
- Well, everybody in town
just adores him.

08:03.206 --> 08:04.827
And he's kept the place going.
- Going?

08:04.896 --> 08:07.034
Going?
What's going around here?

08:07.103 --> 08:10.793
Didn't seem like Hank
is very good at his job.

08:10.862 --> 08:12.655
- Well, you know,
it's still early

08:12.724 --> 08:14.931
and we haven't had a lot
of snowfall this December.

08:15.000 --> 08:18.172
- Sure, yeah.
That's it.

08:18.241 --> 08:20.931
- All right, so why did you
really come home?

08:21.000 --> 08:22.137
Did you come home
for Christmas,

08:22.206 --> 08:24.000
or did you come home
to check on me?

08:24.068 --> 08:26.137
- Do you mind if we talk about
this after I have a shower

08:26.206 --> 08:27.655
over some dinner?

08:27.724 --> 08:29.103
I stink.
- All right.

08:29.172 --> 08:30.896
Well, leave your fancy shoes
out here

08:30.965 --> 08:32.655
and I'll hose them off.

08:32.724 --> 08:34.620
And try to relax!
You're home.

08:34.688 --> 08:37.206
- Okay, okay.

08:37.275 --> 08:40.379
[melancholic music]

08:40.448 --> 08:42.482
- Hey, what'd you bring me?
- Hey.

08:42.551 --> 08:46.034
It's a cranberry kale salad.
- Mmm, looks like Christmas.

08:46.102 --> 08:48.275
- [chuckles]
That's what I was going for.

08:48.344 --> 08:51.068
Hey, did Wyatt make it in okay?
- I guess.

08:51.136 --> 08:53.688
Uh, I was out on
the sleigh ride all afternoon,

08:53.758 --> 08:55.172
and then I fed the horses,
showered,

08:55.241 --> 08:57.896
so I haven't been up
to the ranch house yet.

08:57.965 --> 09:00.517
- Wait, so you haven't
met him yet?

09:00.586 --> 09:02.655
Ooh.
[chuckles]

09:02.724 --> 09:04.517
It's gonna be good.

09:04.586 --> 09:06.275
- No, don't tell me.

09:06.344 --> 09:09.344
Is he one of those guys who
makes little homophobic jokes

09:09.413 --> 09:11.896
without knowing
it makes them look homophobic?

09:11.965 --> 09:13.827
Is he?
'Cause that's awkward.

09:13.896 --> 09:16.862
- Um, no.
Not really.

09:16.931 --> 09:19.206
- So you think we'll get along?

09:19.275 --> 09:21.413
- I think I'm here for it
either way.

09:21.482 --> 09:23.275
Come on.
- All right.

09:27.137 --> 09:29.172
- Hi, Deb.
Brought a salad.

09:29.241 --> 09:31.965
- Oh, thank you, Blake.
- And I brought wine.

09:32.034 --> 09:34.758
- So sweet.
- Where's Wyatt?

09:34.827 --> 09:36.310
- He's just grabbing
a quick shower.

09:36.379 --> 09:37.827
- Washing off the stink
of the city?

09:37.896 --> 09:39.551
[both laugh]
- Nope.

09:39.620 --> 09:41.241
Just some good,
ol' horse manure.

09:41.310 --> 09:43.586
- Ah, Sugar Cube!
- Snow Pea!

09:43.655 --> 09:46.965
Oh, look at you.
- Hi. Thanks.

09:47.034 --> 09:49.689
- Right, 'cause Nutmeg
loves snow peas

09:49.758 --> 09:52.034
and Dasher loves sugar cubes.

09:52.103 --> 09:54.241
Dasher used to be your horse.
- Used to be?

09:54.310 --> 09:57.068
He still is.
- Does he know that?

09:57.137 --> 09:59.172
- [forced laughter]
So tell me everything.

09:59.241 --> 10:00.241
What's new?
What's going on?

10:00.310 --> 10:01.551
How is Sam?

10:01.620 --> 10:03.862
Is he still
with Doctors Without Borders?

10:03.931 --> 10:06.344
- Mm-hmm, he is.
I'm fine, Sam's fine.

10:06.413 --> 10:08.206
- And where is
ol' Dr. Berry anyhow?

10:08.275 --> 10:09.724
- Oh, he's still
in South Africa.

10:09.793 --> 10:11.068
- [groans]
- Yeah.

10:11.137 --> 10:12.655
I was hoping he'd
make it back for Christmas,

10:12.724 --> 10:14.310
but it's not looking so good.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

10:14.379 --> 10:17.241
That's a bummer.
And you must be Hank.

10:17.310 --> 10:19.034
- Heath.
- Heath, Heath.

10:19.103 --> 10:21.172
I don't know why I wanna keep
calling you Hank.

10:21.241 --> 10:23.413
I hope you don't mind
if I mess it up sometimes.

10:23.482 --> 10:26.482
- If you do that,
can I call you Sugar Cube?

10:26.551 --> 10:27.827
[laughter]

10:27.896 --> 10:30.172
- I will work on
getting it right next time.

10:30.241 --> 10:32.413
So Mom, can I help you
with anything?

10:32.482 --> 10:34.172
Oh, you remembered my favorite,

10:34.241 --> 10:35.586
spiced maple
walnut cheesecake--

10:35.655 --> 10:38.137
- Ah, ah, ah, you can have
as much as you want to

10:38.206 --> 10:39.448
after dinner.

10:39.517 --> 10:40.896
- Great, I'll set the table.
- Oh, no, no.

10:40.965 --> 10:42.344
You sit down.
I'll take care of it.

10:42.413 --> 10:44.172
Do you want me
to open this bottle?

10:44.241 --> 10:46.000
Oh, this is actually terrible.

10:46.068 --> 10:48.034
You literally
cannot drink this.

10:48.103 --> 10:51.034
- Yeah, I brought
the terrible wine.

10:51.103 --> 10:52.241
- Oh.

10:52.310 --> 10:55.275
No, I didn't, um...
[clears throat]

10:55.344 --> 10:57.068
I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

10:57.137 --> 10:59.517
This is thick sheepskin.

10:59.586 --> 11:01.931
- [forced laughter]

11:02.000 --> 11:04.620
- He got horse manure
on his fancy shoes

11:04.689 --> 11:07.758
and I think he might be
a little bit cranky.

11:07.827 --> 11:10.103
Let's have dinner.

11:10.172 --> 11:12.827
The wine's good, son.
- Hmm, glad you like it.

11:12.896 --> 11:14.896
Hugh had it sent special
just for you.

11:14.965 --> 11:16.206
- Wow.

11:16.275 --> 11:19.241
So how is that
promotion coming?

11:19.310 --> 11:22.068
- I'm actually in the middle of
this really exciting proposal

11:22.137 --> 11:23.827
for a western expansion.

11:23.896 --> 11:26.310
I've got this angel investor
in Denver who's really into it.

11:26.379 --> 11:27.793
- And what is it you do, Wyatt?

11:27.862 --> 11:29.413
- Financial planning
and venture capital.

11:29.482 --> 11:31.793
- He's a VP
of financial planning

11:31.862 --> 11:34.482
who's well-known for
bringing in angel investors,

11:34.551 --> 11:37.482
which is why it's hard for him
to get home.

11:37.551 --> 11:39.586
- Yeah, this is the
first Christmas we've seen you

11:39.655 --> 11:41.793
in, what, five years?

11:41.862 --> 11:43.620
- Maybe I just wanted
to get you to miss me.

11:43.689 --> 11:46.000
- Oh, is that gonna be your
excuse with Dasher tomorrow

11:46.068 --> 11:47.517
when you say hello to him?

11:47.586 --> 11:49.517
- Actually, I was thinking
about just walking right in

11:49.586 --> 11:51.103
with a sugar cube
peace offering.

11:51.172 --> 11:53.620
- Mm-hmm, well, I hope
it comes with an apology.

11:53.689 --> 11:55.206
- [chuckles]

11:55.275 --> 11:58.931
- I also noticed that
stunning mare outside today.

11:59.000 --> 12:00.758
I didn't know you got yourself
a new draft, Mom.

12:00.827 --> 12:03.689
It must've cost a pretty penny.
- Snowbelle's mine.

12:03.758 --> 12:07.000
I brought her with me
when we moved onto the ranch.

12:09.689 --> 12:11.482
- You live here too?

12:11.551 --> 12:13.482
- Heath moved into
the stable house last year.

12:13.551 --> 12:15.310
He fixed everything up.
He redid the plumbing,

12:15.379 --> 12:18.965
he helps me out with Nutmeg
and down at the vet clinic.

12:19.034 --> 12:21.965
- Wow, a regular
jack-of-all-trades.

12:22.034 --> 12:24.034
- Yeah, venture capital's
up next.

12:24.103 --> 12:26.482
Better watch out.
[laughter]

12:26.551 --> 12:29.931
- Heath has been
a real blessing on the ranch

12:30.000 --> 12:31.724
since Carlos retired.

12:31.793 --> 12:33.620
- Well, we love
being here too,

12:33.689 --> 12:35.275
especially Snow.

12:35.344 --> 12:38.827
She and Dasher are
fairly inseparable.

12:38.896 --> 12:40.310
They're very much in love,
you know?

12:40.379 --> 12:42.793
- They're in love.
Did they tell you that?

12:42.862 --> 12:45.344
- Well, it's true, Wyatt.
[chuckles]

12:45.413 --> 12:47.241
Snowbelle freaked out
the other day

12:47.310 --> 12:48.896
when we were
giving Dash his shot.

12:48.965 --> 12:51.137
She's completely out of control
and overprotective.

12:51.206 --> 12:52.413
It's something to see.

12:52.482 --> 12:54.068
- And he follows her
everywhere she goes.

12:54.137 --> 12:56.379
It's really the cutest thing.

12:56.448 --> 12:58.862
It's like a true equine
romance on the ranch.

12:58.931 --> 13:01.241
I mean,
Christmas carriage riders

13:01.310 --> 13:03.448
just eat it up on the ranch.

13:03.517 --> 13:05.137
- I'm just surprised
that Dasher isn't too old

13:05.206 --> 13:07.103
to carry that sleigh anymore.

13:07.172 --> 13:08.448
- Oh, he's just 15.

13:08.517 --> 13:11.103
And you know Dash lives
for the ride.

13:11.172 --> 13:12.413
- Yeah, I wouldn't worry
too much.

13:12.482 --> 13:14.068
I mean, Dash is a work horse.

13:14.137 --> 13:16.896
He's got, like, a good one
or two years left in him still.

13:16.965 --> 13:19.620
- And a lot more than some
of our woodland critters do.

13:19.689 --> 13:21.586
The gingerbreads
are on their last leg, Deb.

13:21.655 --> 13:23.344
I mean, another storm
and they won't make it,

13:23.413 --> 13:26.482
so we might...

13:26.551 --> 13:28.448
- Oh, no.

13:28.517 --> 13:32.413
Well, maybe we could think
about getting some new ones.

13:32.482 --> 13:34.758
- Or we could think about just

13:34.827 --> 13:38.172
retiring the carriage ride
altogether.

13:38.241 --> 13:40.517
Hmm?

13:40.586 --> 13:43.275
What?
- Wyatt.

13:43.344 --> 13:45.206
Why would you say that?

13:45.275 --> 13:47.724
- Uh...

13:47.793 --> 13:50.482
This ranch is
prime real estate today.

13:50.551 --> 13:54.655
Maybe it's time we think
about finally selling it.

13:54.724 --> 13:58.482
- You think that we should
sell the family ranch?

13:58.551 --> 14:01.620
The home that you grew up in?
- Oh, come on, Mom.

14:01.689 --> 14:03.206
Don't say it like that.

14:03.275 --> 14:05.000
You know that you can't
take care of this place

14:05.068 --> 14:06.206
on our own anymore.

14:06.275 --> 14:08.137
Why not move into the city?
Or town?

14:08.206 --> 14:09.482
Get yourself a little house?

14:09.551 --> 14:11.862
- Wyatt, this is
your mother's home.

14:11.931 --> 14:13.655
- And she's not
taking care of it alone.

14:13.724 --> 14:16.310
- Okay, thank you so much
for your input.

14:16.379 --> 14:17.862
[stammers, clears throat]

14:17.931 --> 14:21.827
I actually brought a few comps
for you to take a look at.

14:21.896 --> 14:25.517
So this is the going rate
for an old ranch like this one.

14:25.586 --> 14:27.862
And the way that this one
is bleeding itself dry,

14:27.931 --> 14:30.172
we'd probably have
another year in it tops.

14:30.241 --> 14:33.931
So...this might not be
the right time to do this,

14:34.000 --> 14:35.793
but I just wanted you
to have it.

14:35.862 --> 14:38.965
- So, um, this is why
you came home for Christmas?

14:39.034 --> 14:41.172
To tell me to sell?
- Of course not.

14:41.241 --> 14:44.103
No, no, that's not--
that's not the only reason.

14:44.172 --> 14:48.103
I--Mom, I know how hard
it is on you.

14:48.172 --> 14:50.275
- You don't know how hard
anything's been on me, son.

14:50.344 --> 14:53.551
You haven't been here.
I, um...

14:53.620 --> 14:56.137
[chuckles weakly]
Please forgive me.

14:56.206 --> 14:58.275
I just...

14:58.344 --> 15:02.275
I think I'm gonna
call it a night.

15:02.344 --> 15:04.034
- Mom, I didn't--
I didn't--

15:04.103 --> 15:05.448
- No, it's fine.

15:05.517 --> 15:07.758
If you get cold, there's
some blankets in the chest

15:07.827 --> 15:09.517
at the end of the bed.

15:09.586 --> 15:11.482
Good night, kids.

15:16.103 --> 15:18.793
- Well, at least you were right

15:18.862 --> 15:22.241
about the wine I brought
not being good.

15:25.655 --> 15:29.344
You really dated that guy
in school?

15:29.413 --> 15:30.827
Ugh.

15:30.896 --> 15:33.517
[owl hooting]

15:33.586 --> 15:36.724
[melancholic music]

15:36.793 --> 15:38.482
- [sighing]

15:41.758 --> 15:43.379
- [yawns]

15:43.448 --> 15:49.724
♪ ♪

15:49.793 --> 15:50.965
Hmm.

16:02.482 --> 16:05.896
[sentimental music]

16:05.965 --> 16:12.482
♪ ♪

16:16.655 --> 16:18.655
[sighs]

16:18.724 --> 16:21.724
[birds chirping]

16:21.793 --> 16:27.586
♪ ♪

16:27.655 --> 16:31.137
[horses braying]

16:33.620 --> 16:36.448
[inhales, exhales]

16:36.517 --> 16:38.034
[chuckles]

16:38.103 --> 16:41.862
Hey, Dash.
You missed me?

16:43.275 --> 16:44.482
[horse neighs]

16:44.551 --> 16:45.965
What's he so mad about?

16:46.034 --> 16:48.793
I didn't know horses
held grudges.

16:48.862 --> 16:50.379
- Oh, so you can talk to horses

16:50.448 --> 16:51.931
and you can tell
when they're angry,

16:52.000 --> 16:53.896
but not when
they're madly in love.

16:53.965 --> 16:56.310
- I wasn't--I didn't--
I don't actually believe

16:56.379 --> 16:58.068
that he thinks about
that kind of stuff.

16:58.137 --> 17:00.827
- Maybe some don't.
Maybe they just feel it.

17:00.896 --> 17:02.310
- Humans are incapable

17:02.379 --> 17:04.344
of loving one person
their entire life.

17:04.413 --> 17:06.482
And a stallion, especially
during breeding season,

17:06.550 --> 17:09.034
I assure you does not know
the meaning of the word.

17:09.103 --> 17:10.896
- Wow, I think you just found

17:10.964 --> 17:12.655
your perfect
Christmas card greeting.

17:12.723 --> 17:15.137
- [forced laughter]
Why did you come here to work?

17:15.205 --> 17:16.689
And I know
it's not for the money.

17:16.758 --> 17:19.792
- Some of us just
like being here.

17:19.862 --> 17:21.964
Not everyone needs more.

17:25.896 --> 17:28.517
[horse neighs]

17:28.586 --> 17:33.827
♪ ♪

17:33.896 --> 17:36.448
- I looked over the proposal.
- Oh.

17:36.517 --> 17:39.655
- And if you wanna sell, fine.

17:39.723 --> 17:41.689
But if I do it,
I'm doing it for you, not me.

17:41.758 --> 17:44.344
- Okay, Mom.
Look.

17:44.413 --> 17:46.205
I'm sorry to just
spring it on you like this,

17:46.275 --> 17:48.034
but property taxes
are coming up,

17:48.103 --> 17:50.000
and of course,
I don't mind helping out.

17:50.068 --> 17:51.378
It's just...

17:51.448 --> 17:55.379
I'm not so sure
that you're still happy here.

17:55.448 --> 17:57.310
I mean, what exactly
are we holding on for?

17:57.379 --> 17:58.758
- What do you mean
I'm not happy?

17:58.827 --> 18:00.862
- I saw your garden
on the way up.

18:00.931 --> 18:03.620
You let it go.

18:03.689 --> 18:05.482
- It's winter.
No one gardens.

18:05.551 --> 18:08.103
- You used to mulch it
and cover it during the winter.

18:08.172 --> 18:09.724
Now it's just a pile of snow.

18:09.793 --> 18:11.724
And your potted hydrangeas
on the porch.

18:11.793 --> 18:13.448
I'm pretty sure
they're dead too.

18:13.517 --> 18:16.310
- They're not dead.
They're hibernating.

18:18.379 --> 18:19.931
- Fine.

18:20.000 --> 18:22.896
When was the last time that you
had friends over for dinner?

18:22.965 --> 18:25.275
- [sighs]

18:25.344 --> 18:27.551
Okay, fine.

18:27.620 --> 18:29.206
I don't want you
paying the taxes anymore.

18:29.275 --> 18:31.310
You work too hard,
and it's not fair,

18:31.379 --> 18:35.034
and it--it seems like you don't
even like coming here anymore.

18:35.103 --> 18:36.379
[sighs]

18:36.448 --> 18:39.586
Maybe it is time
to let the place go.

18:39.655 --> 18:41.517
- Hey, I need you to know
that I didn't just come here

18:41.586 --> 18:43.862
to try to get you
to sell the ranch.

18:43.931 --> 18:45.896
I came because I missed you.

18:45.965 --> 18:47.551
And in some weird way,

18:47.620 --> 18:49.586
I felt like you really
needed me here this year.

18:49.655 --> 18:51.655
- [chuckles]

18:51.724 --> 18:54.724
Well, yeah.

18:54.793 --> 18:57.275
And you're right.

18:57.344 --> 18:58.793
[sighs]

19:02.310 --> 19:04.655
- Did Carlos ever do anything
with that lot next to us?

19:04.724 --> 19:06.482
I thought he was gonna
put a house on it.

19:06.551 --> 19:08.931
- I don't know what Carlos
is doing with that lot

19:09.000 --> 19:12.482
other than letting ragweed
grow all over it.

19:12.551 --> 19:15.758
- Okay, one this way.

19:15.827 --> 19:17.413
Now go with your arms
like this.

19:17.482 --> 19:19.586
Yeah, that's it.
Wait a minute.

19:19.655 --> 19:22.068
- Hank's holiday cheer
strikes again.

19:22.137 --> 19:25.413
- Hey, hey.
You should be nicer to him.

19:25.482 --> 19:28.758
He really has been a savior
here since Carlos retired.

19:28.827 --> 19:30.793
- Mm, well, he certainly
loves swooping in

19:30.862 --> 19:32.551
and being everyone's savior.

19:32.620 --> 19:33.931
- Oh, my goodness.

19:34.000 --> 19:35.724
I have never known you
to be jealous.

19:35.793 --> 19:38.103
But that sounds like jealousy.
- Pfft.

19:38.172 --> 19:40.310
[tuts]
I'm not jealous.

19:40.379 --> 19:41.655
The guy's a horse whisperer.

19:41.724 --> 19:43.655
I seduce millionaires
for all they're worth.

19:43.724 --> 19:45.586
- [scoffs]
- So, Deb.

19:45.655 --> 19:48.206
I really hope you said no
to your son.

19:48.275 --> 19:50.275
- Actually, not that
it's any of your business

19:50.344 --> 19:52.586
as this is a family affair
that does not concern you,

19:52.655 --> 19:56.344
but if you must know,
yes, she is considering it.

19:56.413 --> 20:00.241
- I meant you can't consider
letting your son pay for cocoa.

20:00.310 --> 20:03.034
Have as much as you want.
It's on the house.

20:03.103 --> 20:05.482
Mmm, delicious.

20:05.551 --> 20:07.517
Oh, oh.
You meant the ranch.

20:07.586 --> 20:09.862
Yeah, you shouldn't
sell that either, Deb.

20:09.931 --> 20:11.965
It wouldn't be good
for the horses or the ranch.

20:12.034 --> 20:13.827
Or the business.
- Business?

20:13.896 --> 20:15.413
Business.
What business?

20:15.482 --> 20:18.793
Are you talking about that
tired, old holiday sleigh ride?

20:18.862 --> 20:20.241
How many customers
have you had today?

20:20.310 --> 20:21.586
Was it just the three of them?

20:21.655 --> 20:23.172
And we both know
that kids get in for free,

20:23.241 --> 20:24.931
so what is that, 20 bucks?

20:25.000 --> 20:27.931
- Okay, so the carriage ride
isn't as much of a moneymaker

20:28.000 --> 20:29.482
as it used to be.
So what?

20:29.551 --> 20:31.310
Next year, we're gonna
make a killing on this ranch.

20:31.379 --> 20:32.586
- And how do you propose
to do that?

20:32.655 --> 20:34.724
Because holiday profits
are a bust.

20:34.793 --> 20:36.620
- Well, Heath has an idea

20:36.689 --> 20:39.068
that we could start
teaching riding lessons again.

20:39.137 --> 20:41.965
- And use the free stalls
for horse boarding as well.

20:42.034 --> 20:43.793
There are plenty of people
inside the county line

20:43.862 --> 20:45.206
who would want to board here.

20:45.275 --> 20:47.896
- This place was and always
will be a money pit,

20:47.965 --> 20:49.965
so even if you come up
with some clever,

20:50.034 --> 20:53.965
creative magical way to bring
gross revenues up by 50%,

20:54.034 --> 20:56.172
we will still be
50 in the hole.

20:56.241 --> 20:59.344
So please tell me, where does
that money come from?

21:01.275 --> 21:03.517
[scoffs]

21:03.586 --> 21:05.827
You let me know.

21:05.896 --> 21:07.965
- [sighs]

21:08.034 --> 21:10.448
[gentle music]

21:10.517 --> 21:14.827
♪ ♪

21:14.896 --> 21:16.827
[exhales]

21:28.620 --> 21:32.000
- ♪ O Christmas tree,
o Christmas tree ♪

21:32.068 --> 21:34.172
- That guy's
completely impossible.

21:34.241 --> 21:37.482
He called the ranch
a money pit.

21:37.551 --> 21:39.793
What kind of guy drops a bomb
like that on his mom

21:39.862 --> 21:42.172
at Christmas?

21:42.241 --> 21:44.551
- Okay, uh...
[chuckles]

21:44.620 --> 21:47.310
I didn't mention it before
because it's not my business,

21:47.379 --> 21:50.344
but...

21:50.413 --> 21:52.931
Wyatt is paying
to keep the ranch going.

21:55.206 --> 21:57.586
- [scoffs]
What?

21:57.655 --> 21:59.620
- Yeah.

21:59.689 --> 22:01.689
Wyatt took over
paying the mortgage

22:01.758 --> 22:03.724
and the property taxes
on the ranch

22:03.793 --> 22:06.206
over three years ago now.

22:06.275 --> 22:08.034
- I'm sorry, are you telling me

22:08.103 --> 22:10.137
that Wyatt is the one
keeping us afloat?

22:10.206 --> 22:11.620
- Uh-huh.

22:11.689 --> 22:15.586
He's paying your salary
every month, my vet visits,

22:15.655 --> 22:19.551
not to mention Deb's
ever-growing pile of bills.

22:19.620 --> 22:21.241
- I just...
[scoffs]

22:21.310 --> 22:23.034
I can't believe
I didn't realize it.

22:23.103 --> 22:25.310
I mean, yeah,
it makes sense now.

22:25.379 --> 22:28.206
Of course.
- Hey.

22:28.275 --> 22:29.827
Wyatt didn't want Deb
to throw away

22:29.896 --> 22:31.482
her entire retirement
on the ranch,

22:31.551 --> 22:34.896
so he took over the payments.

22:34.965 --> 22:36.655
He does care.

22:36.724 --> 22:39.862
Even if he is a Scrooge.
- Well, fine.

22:39.931 --> 22:42.103
But it doesn't change the fact
that he's trying to destroy

22:42.172 --> 22:45.931
the one thing his family
worked so hard to build.

22:46.000 --> 22:48.000
Doesn't he know how much
it's gonna crush his mother?

22:48.068 --> 22:49.517
- Yeah, I think
he just believes

22:49.586 --> 22:51.448
he's doing what's best for her,
you know?

22:51.517 --> 22:53.724
- Yeah, yeah, 'cause he thinks
he knows everything.

22:53.793 --> 22:55.379
Everything.
- [chuckles]

22:55.448 --> 22:58.758
- He can't just roll into town
'cause he's this rich city kid

22:58.827 --> 23:01.586
now and start
calling the shots.

23:01.655 --> 23:04.310
I'm not gonna let him.

23:04.379 --> 23:07.344
- What are you
gonna do about it?

23:07.413 --> 23:09.413
- I'll prove him wrong.
- [chuckles]

23:09.482 --> 23:11.206
- Yeah.
[gasps]

23:11.275 --> 23:14.965
Oh, look.

23:15.034 --> 23:18.689
Aren't these just lovely?
- [sighs]

23:18.758 --> 23:21.344
- Look.
- Yeah.

23:29.068 --> 23:30.137
- [sighs]

23:30.206 --> 23:33.206
[kettle whistling]

23:40.896 --> 23:42.413
- Stables don't have
their own stove?

23:42.482 --> 23:44.137
- [groans]
- Oh, sorry.

23:44.206 --> 23:45.931
[stammers, sighs]

23:46.000 --> 23:47.344
I didn't mean
to actually scare you.

23:47.413 --> 23:49.137
Are you okay?
- Yeah.

23:49.206 --> 23:51.000
I'll just go back to
the stable house where I belong

23:51.068 --> 23:52.310
and put this under
some ice water.

23:52.379 --> 23:55.068
- I said I'm sorry.
Can I take a look?

23:55.137 --> 23:57.655
- I brought your mom
an arrangement from town.

23:57.724 --> 24:00.172
And I was gonna sit out
by the tree with some tea

24:00.241 --> 24:02.034
because I don't have a tree
at the stable house.

24:02.103 --> 24:04.551
- It's gotta be
cool or lukewarm.

24:04.620 --> 24:05.827
It can't be ice water.

24:05.896 --> 24:07.551
Will you follow me
to the sink, please?

24:07.620 --> 24:10.482
[chuckles]

24:10.551 --> 24:12.379
- What, you have
a medical degree as well?

24:12.448 --> 24:15.034
- Just put it under there
for a minute.

24:15.103 --> 24:17.689
And no, I don't,
but I did pick up a few things

24:17.758 --> 24:20.448
from Blake's dad
back in the day.

24:20.517 --> 24:23.103
He's a doctor, you know?
- Of course.

24:23.172 --> 24:26.344
Everyone in town goes to him.
He's great.

24:26.413 --> 24:28.241
I'm not sure why he'd let
his daughter date someone

24:28.310 --> 24:29.862
as difficult as you.

24:29.931 --> 24:32.137
- You really think I'm awful,
don't you?

24:32.206 --> 24:36.103
- I think you're in dire need
of some Christmas spirit.

24:36.172 --> 24:38.586
That's for sure.
- Hmm.

24:38.655 --> 24:41.448
[chuckles]

24:41.517 --> 24:44.241
You're not wrong.

24:44.310 --> 24:45.758
I guess--

24:45.827 --> 24:49.517
I guess I am a hard sell
when it comes to Christmas.

24:49.586 --> 24:53.241
They just play that
terrible music for so long.

24:53.310 --> 24:56.413
And after a while, the lights
becoming blinding and--

24:56.482 --> 24:57.862
and in the end,

24:57.931 --> 24:59.689
all the holiday's
really managed to do

24:59.758 --> 25:03.000
is remind you of everything
you wish you had, but don't.

25:03.068 --> 25:06.068
- Wow, yeah,
what's your big holiday wish?

25:06.137 --> 25:08.034
A house in Cape Cod?

25:08.103 --> 25:10.275
Your very own jet plane?
- [laughs]

25:10.344 --> 25:12.862
Now you sound a lot more
like my ex, Lindsey, than me.

25:12.931 --> 25:15.000
- "Lindsey."

25:15.068 --> 25:17.068
Wow, what a lucky woman.

25:17.137 --> 25:19.793
- Luck--man.

25:19.862 --> 25:22.000
A lucky man.

25:22.068 --> 25:25.172
Lindsey's a man
with facial hair like you.

25:25.241 --> 25:27.827
- [scoffs]

25:27.896 --> 25:29.965
You're gay?

25:30.034 --> 25:33.241
- You sound so surprised.

25:33.310 --> 25:35.689
- But you dated Blake
all through school.

25:35.758 --> 25:37.965
- Yeah, I was confused
in high school.

25:38.034 --> 25:40.103
I--I didn't know who I was.

25:40.172 --> 25:42.000
I knew that I loved Blake,

25:42.068 --> 25:44.241
but I think I also knew
that deep down,

25:44.310 --> 25:49.137
the relationship
had a shelf life.

25:49.206 --> 25:53.137
- So when did you
finally come out?

25:53.206 --> 25:56.965
- Around the same time
that I broke up with Blake.

25:57.034 --> 26:00.103
I was moving to New York.
I just graduated.

26:00.172 --> 26:02.931
It wasn't easy growing up here.

26:03.000 --> 26:07.689
Colorado clearly
has its...charms.

26:07.758 --> 26:10.482
But it also has
its difficulties,

26:10.551 --> 26:12.965
especially when it comes
to small towns and locals.

26:13.034 --> 26:14.827
- Oh, yeah.
Don't I know it.

26:14.896 --> 26:17.137
- You out around here too?
Sorry.

26:17.206 --> 26:18.862
I didn't mean to just assume
that you were gay.

26:18.931 --> 26:22.482
It's just--well,
my mom told me and, um...

26:22.551 --> 26:24.655
[both laugh]

26:24.724 --> 26:27.655
Well, your eyes don't lie.
- What?

26:27.724 --> 26:29.068
I didn't check you out
or anything.

26:29.137 --> 26:32.689
- I didn't say you did.
I'm just saying that, uh,

26:32.758 --> 26:36.034
when you know, you know.

26:36.103 --> 26:38.482
- Yeah, well, I guess
I should've known about you too

26:38.551 --> 26:40.551
because if you're not
that into Blake--

26:40.620 --> 26:42.517
- "Well,
then you must love men."

26:42.586 --> 26:44.137
[laughs]
- Yeah.

26:44.206 --> 26:45.344
- That should be good.
Here.

26:45.413 --> 26:48.000
Why don't you wrap it in this?

26:48.068 --> 26:50.551
[gentle music]

26:50.620 --> 26:53.172
- Yeah, it's--thank you.

26:53.241 --> 26:55.034
- Good to go.

26:59.172 --> 27:02.931
How about that tea?

27:03.000 --> 27:04.482
- Okay.

27:08.413 --> 27:10.068
Thank you for this.

27:10.137 --> 27:12.517
- Well, thank you
for taking care of my mom

27:12.586 --> 27:13.931
and this whole place.

27:14.000 --> 27:16.068
She seems to really
appreciate you.

27:16.137 --> 27:19.448
- Yeah, well, I really
appreciate your mom.

27:19.517 --> 27:21.241
And I love this place.

27:21.310 --> 27:23.931
Never really feels like work.

27:24.000 --> 27:25.655
- Why is that?

27:25.724 --> 27:28.689
The ranch?
Why do you love it so much?

27:31.655 --> 27:33.551
- [stammers]

27:33.620 --> 27:35.965
When I was 12 years old,

27:36.034 --> 27:40.931
my dad took off with some woman
he'd met at a work conference.

27:41.000 --> 27:44.931
I didn't really understand
what that meant at the time,

27:45.000 --> 27:47.827
but I do remember
it was summer,

27:47.896 --> 27:51.068
and the vacations
we used to take as a family

27:51.137 --> 27:54.103
suddenly stopped.

27:54.172 --> 27:58.103
And my mom,
well, she cried a lot.

27:58.172 --> 28:00.862
I remember her crying
from her room at night,

28:00.931 --> 28:04.862
even after she thought
I'd fallen asleep.

28:04.931 --> 28:07.172
After a few months,
it wasn't every night anymore,

28:07.241 --> 28:09.931
but every other day,

28:10.000 --> 28:12.448
it would happen again.

28:12.517 --> 28:15.137
And I knew she wasn't
any better.

28:15.206 --> 28:17.586
And then, Christmastime came,

28:17.655 --> 28:20.827
and I thought
it would be so hard,

28:20.896 --> 28:25.517
but one night,
she bundled me up in a snowsuit

28:25.586 --> 28:28.103
and brought us here.

28:28.172 --> 28:30.517
I had no idea
where we were going,

28:30.586 --> 28:35.103
but when we showed up
to the carriage ride...

28:35.172 --> 28:37.344
[exhales]

28:37.413 --> 28:39.655
It was like

28:39.724 --> 28:42.517
a whole new world.

28:42.586 --> 28:46.103
The lights and the horses,

28:46.172 --> 28:50.344
people everywhere.

28:50.413 --> 28:52.172
Happy people.

28:52.241 --> 28:54.379
- Yeah.

28:54.448 --> 28:57.758
I remember when this place was
something special to the town.

28:57.827 --> 28:59.931
To all the neighboring counties
as well.

29:00.000 --> 29:02.758
It was...
[sighs]

29:02.827 --> 29:05.931
It was my father's
pride and joy.

29:06.000 --> 29:08.241
So your mom
loved the place too, huh?

29:08.310 --> 29:11.068
- She did.

29:11.137 --> 29:13.482
We were so happy that night.

29:13.551 --> 29:16.586
Yeah, we curled up
under the blankets and--

29:16.655 --> 29:20.655
and we were just taken away.

29:20.724 --> 29:23.034
[sighs]

29:23.103 --> 29:25.724
You know what?
That Christmas,

29:25.793 --> 29:27.931
she started getting
better and better.

29:28.000 --> 29:30.172
I think this place gave her
a little hope again.

29:30.241 --> 29:32.793
I, of course,
loved this place too,

29:32.862 --> 29:35.620
so we came back
every year after.

29:35.689 --> 29:38.482
- What does she think about you
running the place now?

29:38.551 --> 29:40.241
- She's gone.

29:40.310 --> 29:43.103
Almost three years now.

29:43.172 --> 29:45.724
- I'm sorry.

29:45.793 --> 29:47.896
- Thank you.

29:47.965 --> 29:51.931
[sighs]
Anyway...

29:52.000 --> 29:55.103
I think I should get back
to my place.

29:55.172 --> 29:57.448
- Okay.

29:57.517 --> 30:00.310
- Thank you.

30:00.379 --> 30:02.931
- Good night.
- Night.

30:07.241 --> 30:10.103
[melancholic music]

30:10.172 --> 30:11.896
♪ ♪

30:11.965 --> 30:14.275
- Hey, Dash.

30:14.344 --> 30:18.275
Good boy.

30:18.344 --> 30:20.827
I'm sorry I've been away
for so long.

30:20.896 --> 30:27.931
♪ ♪

30:31.724 --> 30:33.517
But you know what?

30:33.586 --> 30:35.896
It's Christmastime,

30:35.965 --> 30:38.620
and I think I deserve
a second chance.

30:41.068 --> 30:42.448
Yeah, I knew
that would get you.

30:42.517 --> 30:44.724
[Dash whinnies]

30:47.620 --> 30:50.620
[chuckles]
I missed you too.

30:50.689 --> 30:52.034
[laughs]

30:52.103 --> 30:53.620
[clicks tongue]

30:59.310 --> 31:01.172
- Oh, if it isn't
ol' Dasher

31:01.241 --> 31:03.862
and Mr. Sugar Cube
coming out to play.

31:03.931 --> 31:06.344
- You call me Sugar Cube,
I'ma call you Apple Sauce.

31:06.413 --> 31:08.931
Mom told me about her thing
for apples.

31:09.000 --> 31:11.310
- That's Apple Slice to you.
- Sure, whatever you say.

31:11.379 --> 31:13.103
You heading up the trail,
Apple Sauce?

31:13.172 --> 31:16.482
- Well, I gotta check
if everything survived

31:16.551 --> 31:19.551
in the storm last night.

31:19.620 --> 31:22.068
- You mind if we tag along?
- Hope you can keep up.

31:22.137 --> 31:23.896
- Did you hear that?

31:23.965 --> 31:26.344
[mellow music]

31:26.413 --> 31:33.413
♪ ♪

31:42.655 --> 31:44.896
So right up there--
- Uh-huh.

31:44.965 --> 31:47.689
- That's where I used
to hang out when I was a kid.

31:47.758 --> 31:49.275
- Oh, really?
- Uh-huh.

31:49.344 --> 31:51.206
And I would get
all my friends together

31:51.275 --> 31:54.517
and we would go camping
and fishing all weekend long.

31:54.586 --> 31:56.137
- Mm.

32:06.862 --> 32:11.413
Look, I had no idea you were
the one keeping this place up.

32:11.482 --> 32:12.827
- Well, I would've kept it up

32:12.896 --> 32:15.206
if I thought my mom
could keep this place going.

32:15.275 --> 32:17.413
- I understand you do
what you have to do.

32:17.482 --> 32:21.275
It's just...
it's hard to imagine

32:21.344 --> 32:23.724
this will all be gone someday.

32:23.793 --> 32:25.310
- Well, nothing lasts forever,
right?

32:25.379 --> 32:28.103
- Some things do.
Life, death.

32:28.172 --> 32:30.310
The seasons changing.

32:30.379 --> 32:31.931
Snowbelle being faster
than Dash.

32:32.000 --> 32:33.793
- Huh?
- That's forever. Let's go.

32:33.862 --> 32:35.068
- Come on.
- Come on, come on.

32:35.137 --> 32:38.068
[sentimental music]

32:38.137 --> 32:44.241
♪ ♪

32:45.379 --> 32:47.655
[door opens]
- Hello?

32:47.724 --> 32:49.689
- Ooh!

32:49.758 --> 32:53.000
Well, if it isn't Harmony
Springs' homecoming queen

32:53.068 --> 32:55.310
coming back to pass down
the crown again.

32:55.379 --> 32:57.793
- Thank you.
[both laugh]

32:57.862 --> 32:59.517
What are you working on?
- Oh.

32:59.586 --> 33:00.965
I'm just putting together
some stuff

33:01.034 --> 33:04.172
for this prospective realtor
I spoke to this morning.

33:04.241 --> 33:07.137
She says that we can
have the ranch sold

33:07.206 --> 33:10.137
just after the new year.

33:10.206 --> 33:11.551
[sighs]

33:11.620 --> 33:12.965
- Well, you're gonna have
to stop that now

33:13.034 --> 33:14.344
'cause we're going
to the Stampede tonight,

33:14.413 --> 33:15.689
and you are coming with us.

33:15.758 --> 33:17.793
- Uh-uh.
- Yup, yes.

33:17.862 --> 33:19.448
You are.
Come on, Deb.

33:19.517 --> 33:21.000
You and I, we never get out.

33:21.068 --> 33:22.862
Wyatt is finally home
for Christmas

33:22.931 --> 33:26.000
and the old gang
is gonna come join us.

33:26.068 --> 33:29.103
It'll be good for you.
For all of us.

33:29.172 --> 33:30.758
- Uh...
- Mm-hmm.

33:30.827 --> 33:33.448
- [laughs]
- Yeah? Yeah--oh!

33:33.517 --> 33:35.344
- Well, I'm changing
my clothes.

33:35.413 --> 33:38.931
- [gasps]
We're going dancing.

33:39.000 --> 33:41.482
- Absolutely not.
I'm gonna go take a shower.

33:41.551 --> 33:43.206
- Uh, and put on
your dancing shoes.

33:43.275 --> 33:45.793
Come on, Wy.
Deb's coming.

33:45.862 --> 33:47.206
You have to.

33:47.275 --> 33:49.517
- Uh, the only thing
I have to do is go to sleep.

33:49.586 --> 33:51.551
Do you have any idea
how sore my legs are

33:51.620 --> 33:53.827
from riding all day?

33:53.896 --> 33:55.724
What--no.
Answer is no.

33:55.793 --> 33:57.137
I am not going.
End of story.

33:57.206 --> 33:58.689
Why are you still
looking at me like that?

33:58.758 --> 34:01.310
- If I'm going, you're going.

34:03.448 --> 34:06.068
- We're really doing this?
- Yup.

34:06.137 --> 34:07.724
- Okay.

34:07.793 --> 34:10.724
[country music]

34:10.793 --> 34:12.757
♪ ♪

34:12.827 --> 34:15.379
- [gasps, screams]

34:15.447 --> 34:17.551
- Ah, as I live and breathe!

34:17.620 --> 34:20.103
Our star cheerleader.
Wow, look at you.

34:20.172 --> 34:23.585
You haven't aged a bit.
- And I still got the moves.

34:23.655 --> 34:25.896
Do you?
- No, I don't dance anymore.

34:25.965 --> 34:28.688
But that is what
this handsome hubby is for.

34:28.757 --> 34:30.379
Congratulations.
- Aw!

34:30.447 --> 34:33.068
The old gang back together!
- It took only, what?

34:33.137 --> 34:34.585
Like 100 years.

34:34.655 --> 34:36.688
- She never was
very good at math.

34:36.757 --> 34:38.793
- Excuse me,
I meant in dog years, duh.

34:38.862 --> 34:39.965
'Cause you're in the doghouse

34:40.034 --> 34:41.172
for taking too long
to come home.

34:41.241 --> 34:42.896
- All right, fine, well,
how about I buy

34:42.965 --> 34:44.585
the first round of shots
to make it up to you?

34:44.655 --> 34:46.241
- It's gonna take three
to make it up to me.

34:46.310 --> 34:47.413
- [laughs]

34:47.482 --> 34:50.034
all: Cheers.

34:50.103 --> 34:52.275
- Mmm, mmm.
- Mmm.

34:52.344 --> 34:53.757
[coughs]
- Whoo.

34:53.827 --> 34:56.206
- Wait, you should've seen
Wyatt back in high school.

34:56.275 --> 34:59.310
He was Mr. Big Shot.
- And Blake was Mrs. Big Shot.

34:59.379 --> 35:01.172
- Oh, and I was just
Ms. Perfect Girl in School.

35:01.241 --> 35:02.482
No big deal.
- Oh, yeah.

35:02.551 --> 35:04.965
Lil' Ms. Perfect over here,
who as I recall,

35:05.034 --> 35:08.447
got suspended for organizing
our senior skip day.

35:08.516 --> 35:10.068
- Um, excuse me?

35:10.137 --> 35:11.620
Just because you had
perfect attendance

35:11.688 --> 35:13.896
and got straight A's does not
make you some Mr. Perfect.

35:13.965 --> 35:15.068
- That's not the half of it.

35:15.137 --> 35:16.827
Wyatt was wild
back in high school.

35:16.896 --> 35:19.551
- So is that why you guys
were so damn crazy about me?

35:19.620 --> 35:21.655
- [sighs, snorts]

35:21.724 --> 35:23.172
- But you weren't out
at all then, right?

35:23.241 --> 35:25.413
- Oh, he came out in the middle
of his graduation speech

35:25.482 --> 35:26.862
to the class.

35:26.931 --> 35:28.620
Shocked the town with that one.
- Yeah.

35:28.688 --> 35:31.172
Only that was his coming out
to me too.

35:31.241 --> 35:33.793
I mean, we'd been broken up
for a while, but...

35:33.862 --> 35:36.620
[sighs] Then he just sprung it
on me with everybody else.

35:36.688 --> 35:37.931
That's Wyatt for you.

35:38.000 --> 35:39.482
Always knows how to take you
for a real spin.

35:39.551 --> 35:40.757
- All right, all right.
I'm sorry.

35:40.827 --> 35:41.931
I was a bit of a mess.

35:42.000 --> 35:44.206
I was a little confused
back then.

35:44.275 --> 35:45.862
But just for the record,
I was not that wild.

35:45.931 --> 35:48.620
I was a very, very good boy.

35:48.689 --> 35:50.344
Mostly.
- It's true.

35:50.413 --> 35:52.206
He can be a sweetie
when he wants to be.

35:52.275 --> 35:53.793
Wait, do you remember
when Danny broke up with me

35:53.862 --> 35:55.275
right before homecoming,

35:55.344 --> 35:57.344
and Wyatt took us both
to the dance together?

35:57.413 --> 36:00.068
He took turns dancing
with each of us.

36:00.137 --> 36:03.275
But that was before
Ryan and I were together.

36:03.344 --> 36:05.965
Mm-hmm, we were
just friends then.

36:06.034 --> 36:08.034
- Also for the record,
I have never danced with a boy

36:08.103 --> 36:10.172
the way that I danced
with you two that night.

36:10.241 --> 36:11.413
- Hmm.

36:11.482 --> 36:13.206
- Have you even
danced with a boy at all,

36:13.275 --> 36:15.413
Mr. Boot Scootin' Boogie?

36:15.482 --> 36:18.068
- No, no,
these two ladies ruined me.

36:18.137 --> 36:19.689
I haven't been
to a dance since.

36:19.758 --> 36:22.724
- Aw.
- Oh, that's too bad.

36:22.793 --> 36:26.551
I say, let's dance.
- Whoo, yes!

36:26.620 --> 36:28.000
- I'm gonna sit this one out,

36:28.068 --> 36:30.206
but who wants to play
a little holiday horseshoe?

36:30.275 --> 36:32.034
- You're on.

36:32.103 --> 36:33.793
- Wait up, lover boy.

36:33.862 --> 36:36.206
[excited chatter]
- Whoo!

36:36.275 --> 36:38.482
- [laughs]
- Whoo!

36:38.551 --> 36:41.689
- Okay.
Here we go.

36:41.758 --> 36:44.689
[overlapping chatter]

36:44.758 --> 36:47.482
[rock music]

36:47.551 --> 36:49.379
- Yes!

36:49.448 --> 36:51.103
- How do you know
which way to turn?

36:51.172 --> 36:54.448
[indistinct chatter]

36:59.758 --> 37:02.103
- Oh, oh!
Ha!

37:02.172 --> 37:05.068
[ball clanks]
both: [cheers]

37:05.137 --> 37:07.586
- Hi, can I get two
sauvignon blancs, please?

37:07.655 --> 37:09.068
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

37:09.137 --> 37:10.896
- I'll have one too.
- [gasps] Yes.

37:10.965 --> 37:12.482
[laughter]

37:12.551 --> 37:14.275
- So when's Sam coming home?

37:14.344 --> 37:16.827
- He's saying not until
after the new year.

37:16.896 --> 37:19.827
- Aw, honey, I'm sorry, but
it'll be before you know it.

37:19.896 --> 37:22.413
- Deb, Blake,
nice to see you both.

37:22.482 --> 37:24.586
Now put those on my tab.

37:24.655 --> 37:27.275
- Ah, thanks, Carlos.
- Carlos, thank you.

37:27.344 --> 37:28.896
Merry Christmas.
- Well, thank you, Blake.

37:28.965 --> 37:32.413
Merry Christmas.

37:32.482 --> 37:34.586
- Actually, I'm gonna run
to the ladies' room,

37:34.655 --> 37:38.482
but I'll catch up with you
in a few.

37:38.551 --> 37:43.275
- Well, so how are George,
and Gina, and the grandkids?

37:43.344 --> 37:46.137
- Well, Gina's still working
on her PhD online

37:46.206 --> 37:47.413
and staying home with the kids

37:47.482 --> 37:49.517
and George is supervising
at the lumberyard,

37:49.586 --> 37:51.068
but only a couple days
a week now.

37:51.137 --> 37:53.241
- Please tell them
I said hello.

37:53.310 --> 37:55.758
- I sure will.
And Wyatt?

37:55.827 --> 37:59.103
- Oh, actually Wyatt's here!
He came home for the holidays.

37:59.172 --> 38:00.862
He's right over there.
[chuckles]

38:00.931 --> 38:02.862
- Well, I'll be.
[laughs]

38:02.931 --> 38:04.931
- Yeah.
- Finally, little fox.

38:05.000 --> 38:08.344
That's great news.
- [sighs] Yeah.

38:08.413 --> 38:11.586
- How about you?
How's Ms. Deb?

38:11.655 --> 38:13.758
- Oh, I'm just
an old spinster now.

38:13.827 --> 38:17.172
You know, I've taken up
knitting and crocheting.

38:17.241 --> 38:20.620
- A little tapestry work?
- Yeah.

38:20.689 --> 38:24.448
I, uh...I'm thinking
about selling the ranch.

38:24.517 --> 38:27.068
- What?
Deb, no.

38:27.137 --> 38:30.137
- Yeah, Wyatt thinks
it's probably too much

38:30.206 --> 38:32.931
for me to keep up, and I'm
starting to think he's right.

38:33.000 --> 38:34.413
- What about the horses?

38:34.482 --> 38:36.655
- Well, Dasher would have
to go to some stable somewhere

38:36.724 --> 38:38.655
and the rest will just
have to go elsewhere.

38:38.724 --> 38:41.448
- Is that what you really want?

38:41.517 --> 38:43.310
- I don't know what I want.

38:43.379 --> 38:46.172
All I know is I don't wanna
be a burden to my son.

38:48.551 --> 38:49.758
[sighs]

38:49.827 --> 38:51.655
- What do you say
to a retired ranch hand

38:51.724 --> 38:55.379
taking this old spinster
for a little holiday spin?

38:55.448 --> 38:58.793
- [laughs]
Let's do it.

39:04.379 --> 39:06.379
- Do you see Deb with Carlos?
- Mm-hmm.

39:06.448 --> 39:07.448
- [chuckles]

39:12.068 --> 39:14.103
Wyatt, why don't you
take Heath for a spin?

39:14.172 --> 39:16.379
- At Stampede?
Are you crazy?

39:16.448 --> 39:20.413
No offense, but no.
- Why not?

39:20.482 --> 39:22.275
[groans]
Screw what anyone else thinks.

39:22.344 --> 39:25.068
If someone has a problem
with it, they'll answer to me.

39:25.137 --> 39:26.551
Plus, you know
you love to dance.

39:26.620 --> 39:28.586
- Sure, yeah, but not
a slow dance with another dude

39:28.655 --> 39:31.896
at a straight country barn.

39:31.965 --> 39:35.000
- Well, then,
you can dance with me.

39:35.068 --> 39:36.931
Right now.
- Mm.

39:37.000 --> 39:39.689
- Right now.
- Mm-mm-mm.

39:39.758 --> 39:42.586
- Come on.

39:42.655 --> 39:45.586
[music playing]

39:45.655 --> 39:52.689
♪ ♪

40:08.689 --> 40:11.137
Aw.
- All right.

40:11.206 --> 40:12.931
- You should've asked him
to dance.

40:13.000 --> 40:15.034
- He doesn't wanna dance.
- [sighs]

40:15.103 --> 40:17.068
You're not really
that clueless, are you?

40:17.137 --> 40:19.413
- He doesn't even like me.
- Wrong.

40:19.482 --> 40:20.689
He doesn't like that

40:20.758 --> 40:22.034
you're trying to get Deb
to sell the ranch.

40:22.103 --> 40:24.068
You, he definitely likes.

40:24.137 --> 40:26.275
He just--
he doesn't know it yet.

40:26.344 --> 40:29.793
The real question is,
you like him too?

40:29.862 --> 40:31.482
Your poker face
is better than his.

40:31.551 --> 40:32.965
- [laughs]

40:34.758 --> 40:37.206
He's obviously cute.
- Mm-hmm.

40:37.275 --> 40:40.862
- Just a bit standoffish.
- That's a defense mechanism.

40:40.931 --> 40:43.448
Heath,
he's never had a boyfriend,

40:43.517 --> 40:45.758
not that there are a lot
of options in this town,

40:45.827 --> 40:47.931
and certainly no one
in his league.

40:48.000 --> 40:50.689
- I'm not so convinced that he
wants those walls broken down.

40:50.758 --> 40:53.896
- Maybe he's just
protecting his heart,

40:53.965 --> 40:56.034
making sure you're worth it.

40:56.103 --> 40:57.551
He's not cold-hearted like you.

40:57.620 --> 41:00.241
- Oh, so I'm cold-hearted now.
- Mmm, yeah, you--

41:00.310 --> 41:02.965
- [laughs]
- Maybe.

41:03.034 --> 41:04.655
- You're not still mad about
what happened in high school,

41:04.724 --> 41:08.000
are you?

41:08.068 --> 41:11.068
- I was mad you didn't
tell me, Wy.

41:11.137 --> 41:13.379
I mean, it didn't matter
that we were together.

41:13.448 --> 41:15.448
You're my best friend.

41:15.517 --> 41:17.275
And at some point,
I was pretty sure

41:17.344 --> 41:18.517
I knew something was up,

41:18.586 --> 41:20.689
and thought I knew
what that something was,

41:20.758 --> 41:25.413
but I wasn't mad at you
for that.

41:25.482 --> 41:28.793
I was mad because I wanted
to hear it from you,

41:28.862 --> 41:30.275
not in front of a crowd.

41:30.344 --> 41:33.689
- I get it.
I'm sorry.

41:33.758 --> 41:36.000
I know I can be a--
- Jerk sometimes?

41:36.068 --> 41:38.344
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

41:38.413 --> 41:39.448
- Forgive me?

41:39.517 --> 41:42.068
- I forgave you
a long time ago.

41:42.137 --> 41:45.655
Just don't make that mistake
again, okay?

41:45.724 --> 41:48.344
Next time you meet
someone special,

41:48.413 --> 41:51.137
be honest with them.

41:51.206 --> 41:53.689
And yourself.
- Okay.

41:53.758 --> 41:55.620
- [chuckles]

41:58.000 --> 42:01.241
[applause]

42:01.310 --> 42:04.344
[all cheering]

42:04.413 --> 42:05.586
- I'ma get a drink.
- Oh, my God.

42:05.655 --> 42:07.068
Wyatt.
- What?

42:07.137 --> 42:10.551
- Yeah!
[laughs]

42:10.620 --> 42:12.275
Ha!
Yeah!

42:12.344 --> 42:14.034
Whoo.

42:14.103 --> 42:15.827
[laughs]

42:15.896 --> 42:17.068
- There it is.
- Look ahead.

42:17.137 --> 42:18.379
- Look ahead.
Don't let it leave you.

42:18.448 --> 42:20.689
[onlookers whooping]
Come on, there you go.

42:20.758 --> 42:22.034
- Come on, please.
- All right.

42:22.103 --> 42:23.724
- It'll be fun.

42:23.793 --> 42:25.413
- All right, all right.
- Come on!

42:25.482 --> 42:32.482
♪ ♪

43:03.241 --> 43:07.379
- Whoo-hoo!
[laughs]

43:11.827 --> 43:14.965
- It looks like someone's
done this once or twice before.

43:15.034 --> 43:18.068
Finally remembering your roots,
Sugar Cube? [laughs]

43:18.137 --> 43:19.517
- Maybe they were
just hibernating

43:19.586 --> 43:21.931
under the snow for a while.

43:28.310 --> 43:30.000
[birds chirping]

43:35.689 --> 43:37.137
- [sighs]

43:50.793 --> 43:51.896
[bell jangles]

43:51.965 --> 43:53.310
- Whoa!
- Hey.

43:53.379 --> 43:56.068
- Yeah, the hot water is out
at the stable house.

43:56.137 --> 43:58.034
- Cool--that's good.
Um, sorry, I didn't mean to...

43:58.103 --> 44:00.068
I just--take your time.
I'll come back.

44:00.137 --> 44:01.655
[stammers]
I'll use the one down the hall.

44:01.724 --> 44:02.827
- ...A moment.

44:02.896 --> 44:04.724
- It's--sorry.
It's this way.

44:17.344 --> 44:19.551
You're using the wrong glue.

44:19.620 --> 44:22.172
Try this.

44:22.241 --> 44:24.413
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

44:33.000 --> 44:35.724
You know, my parents
built this entire place

44:35.793 --> 44:37.586
from the ground up.

44:37.655 --> 44:40.689
It was just a big,
beautiful, naked 100 acres

44:40.758 --> 44:42.103
before they showed up.

44:42.172 --> 44:43.482
- Back in '86.

44:43.551 --> 44:45.793
With the money your dad
inherited from his father

44:45.862 --> 44:47.275
when he died in Vietnam.

44:47.344 --> 44:49.551
- Wow, somebody knows
their Burwall family history.

44:49.620 --> 44:51.413
- Yeah, I feel like
Wayne was the father

44:51.482 --> 44:54.551
I always wished I'd had.

44:54.620 --> 44:56.896
You know, I remember him
from the rides.

44:56.965 --> 44:58.448
He used to always
tell you the difference

44:58.517 --> 45:01.482
between a ponderosa
and a lodgepole pine.

45:01.551 --> 45:05.241
And he had this very loud,
infectious laugh, didn't he?

45:05.310 --> 45:07.655
- [laughs]
Yes, it was a cackle.

45:07.724 --> 45:10.034
My mom used to say that
it could fill an entire room

45:10.103 --> 45:12.310
with happy.

45:12.379 --> 45:15.448
I used to help him man the ride
when I was a kid.

45:17.793 --> 45:21.724
- You know what?
I think I remember you from it.

45:21.793 --> 45:25.310
Did you used to wear, like,
a--a tan lambskin jacket?

45:25.379 --> 45:26.827
- Yeah.
Yeah, that was me.

45:26.896 --> 45:29.413
And a very attractive
chili bowl haircut too.

45:29.482 --> 45:31.827
- [chuckles]
Yeah.

45:31.896 --> 45:34.034
I was a little older than you,

45:34.103 --> 45:37.827
but I remember you at the front
on the carriage, both of you.

45:37.896 --> 45:40.206
You were good with horses too.

45:40.275 --> 45:42.724
- Not as good as you.

45:42.793 --> 45:44.896
- Oh, I had no idea
about horses back then.

45:44.965 --> 45:48.724
But I could tell you did.
And, you know what?

45:48.793 --> 45:51.172
I--I remember
when you both stopped

45:51.241 --> 45:52.862
manning the rides altogether.

45:52.931 --> 45:56.137
It was...it was weird.

45:56.206 --> 45:59.034
I'm sorry your father passed.

45:59.103 --> 46:01.758
- Yeah, well, things change,
don't they?

46:01.827 --> 46:04.758
[gentle music]

46:04.827 --> 46:06.034
♪ ♪

46:06.103 --> 46:09.137
- That wood cross,

46:09.206 --> 46:12.586
um, with the old cowboy hat
by the fence line,

46:12.655 --> 46:14.862
your dad?

46:14.931 --> 46:17.758
- It was his thinking spot.

46:17.827 --> 46:20.275
I put it up there
when he passed.

46:20.344 --> 46:22.793
It's got some of his ashes too.

46:22.862 --> 46:24.413
- It could use some tidying up.

46:24.482 --> 46:28.689
If you wanted to pay a visit,
I could help you.

46:28.758 --> 46:31.896
- Thanks.

46:31.965 --> 46:34.896
[inhales]
So what about you?

46:34.965 --> 46:36.758
What were you like
when you were a kid?

46:36.827 --> 46:38.896
Before your dad took off?
- Oh.

46:38.965 --> 46:40.689
We moved around a lot
when I was a kid.

46:40.758 --> 46:42.758
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah.

46:42.827 --> 46:45.344
Mom and dad moved us here
from Colombia

46:45.413 --> 46:49.586
when I was 10,
two years before he left.

46:49.655 --> 46:54.034
And...we were never close
to my mom's family.

46:54.103 --> 46:56.758
In fact, I don't think
she liked them very much.

46:56.827 --> 46:59.758
She never really spoke
about them when we moved.

46:59.827 --> 47:01.137
- Well, it sounds like
the two of you

47:01.206 --> 47:03.517
did a pretty good job
on your own.

47:03.586 --> 47:05.862
- Yeah, we did.
[chuckles]

47:05.931 --> 47:09.206
We found a home here
in Harmony Springs,

47:09.275 --> 47:13.448
so I guess life, in the end,
took us where we belonged.

47:17.275 --> 47:21.827
- And what about boyfriends?
You ever have any of those?

47:21.896 --> 47:24.862
- Yeah, I've never been
a heartbreaker like you.

47:26.241 --> 47:29.551
- Uh, excuse me?

47:29.620 --> 47:32.379
And what's that
supposed to mean?

47:32.448 --> 47:34.551
- Well, when I found out
you were gay,

47:34.620 --> 47:37.827
I asked Blake about your ex,
and she ended up

47:37.896 --> 47:41.413
telling me about Max,
and Steve, John--

47:41.482 --> 47:43.103
- Okay.
[chuckles]

47:43.172 --> 47:44.620
- Pretty much everyone
after Blake.

47:44.689 --> 47:47.310
- I asked if you ever had one.

47:47.379 --> 47:50.310
- Yes, there was someone
back in college.

47:50.379 --> 47:51.689
Cameron.

47:51.758 --> 47:53.310
But he wasn't really
my boyfriend,

47:53.379 --> 47:55.241
so I don't--I don't think so.

47:55.310 --> 47:57.965
- Why not?

47:58.034 --> 48:01.137
- I thought it was something,
but turns out,

48:01.206 --> 48:04.931
it was something different
for him.

48:05.000 --> 48:08.724
I had this big holiday day
to plan for us

48:08.793 --> 48:10.896
over Christmas break.

48:10.965 --> 48:13.827
I got bison chili,
and cheap champagne,

48:13.896 --> 48:15.379
and blankets,

48:15.448 --> 48:18.862
and I put up a projector
outside of the dorm

48:18.931 --> 48:20.034
to watch old Christmas movies.

48:20.103 --> 48:21.586
- Oh, that's so sweet.

48:21.655 --> 48:23.758
Did you have
"A Christmas Story"?

48:23.827 --> 48:25.689
- Oh, yeah,
and "It's a Wonderful Life."

48:25.758 --> 48:27.310
My favorite.

48:27.379 --> 48:30.517
Anyway, some of his buddies
saw me trying to surprise him

48:30.586 --> 48:35.206
and they started
calling us names.

48:35.275 --> 48:36.586
He freaked out.

48:36.655 --> 48:38.931
He pretended like
he didn't know me

48:39.000 --> 48:41.137
to save himself
from being outed.

48:41.206 --> 48:44.689
- That's awful.
What an ass.

48:44.758 --> 48:47.310
- Yeah, but it's on me too.

48:47.379 --> 48:50.482
I knew he wasn't out.

48:50.551 --> 48:51.758
[scoffs]

48:51.827 --> 48:53.482
I thought doing
something special for him

48:53.551 --> 48:56.413
would make him change his mind

48:56.482 --> 48:58.827
or see things differently.

48:58.896 --> 49:01.241
I was stupid.
[sighs]

49:01.310 --> 49:03.551
I really thought I loved him,
you know?

49:05.862 --> 49:07.137
[inhales]

49:07.206 --> 49:08.931
That doesn't sound much
like love, does it?

49:09.000 --> 49:12.103
- No.
No, that definitely doesn't.

49:12.172 --> 49:15.068
- I got kicked in the gut,

49:15.137 --> 49:18.793
so it's made it hard for me
to talk to guys.

49:18.862 --> 49:21.586
- Well, you're talking to me
just fine.

49:21.655 --> 49:24.517
Anyhow, screw Cameron.

49:24.586 --> 49:27.551
You deserve a lot better
than that.

49:27.620 --> 49:30.172
[gentle music]

49:30.241 --> 49:33.758
♪ ♪

49:33.827 --> 49:35.310
All right.

49:40.000 --> 49:43.965
Hmm, they still look broken.
- [scoffs]

49:44.034 --> 49:47.344
Broken, but happy
to have each other.

49:49.517 --> 49:50.827
- [chuckles]

50:03.793 --> 50:08.379
chorus: ♪ All is calm ♪

50:08.448 --> 50:12.896
♪ All is bright ♪

50:12.965 --> 50:17.275
♪ 'Round yon virgin ♪

50:17.344 --> 50:21.931
♪ Mother and child ♪

50:22.000 --> 50:25.758
♪ Holy infant ♪

50:25.827 --> 50:31.000
♪ So tender and mild ♪

50:31.068 --> 50:34.137
♪ Sleep in ♪

50:34.206 --> 50:40.482
♪ Heavenly peace ♪

50:40.551 --> 50:43.344
♪ Sleep in ♪

50:43.413 --> 50:47.103
♪ Heavenly peace ♪

50:47.172 --> 50:49.896
♪ ♪

50:49.965 --> 50:52.827
♪ Silent night ♪

50:52.896 --> 50:55.310
[acoustic version
of "Silent Night"]

50:55.379 --> 51:02.448
♪ ♪

51:07.689 --> 51:10.517
- Evening.
- Oh, Carlos.

51:10.586 --> 51:12.206
- It was nice dancing
with you the other night.

51:12.275 --> 51:14.310
- Yeah, that was really lovely.

51:14.379 --> 51:16.517
No, it was nice to catch up.

51:16.586 --> 51:18.724
Old times with old friends.

51:18.793 --> 51:21.551
- Well, I'd like
to do it again.

51:21.620 --> 51:24.413
Maybe take you out to dinner
sometime soon?

51:24.482 --> 51:28.206
- Oh, um, it's probably
not a good time.

51:28.275 --> 51:30.965
- Because you're selling
the ranch?

51:31.034 --> 51:33.206
Deb, I tried calling you
a bunch of times.

51:33.275 --> 51:35.068
You're always busy.

51:35.137 --> 51:37.931
You can't always have
some excuse, Deb.

51:38.000 --> 51:39.482
I know we both feel
the same way,

51:39.551 --> 51:43.034
so why'd you stop
taking my calls?

51:43.103 --> 51:47.551
I retired hoping that
we could, I don't know,

51:47.620 --> 51:49.827
find something special for us.

51:49.896 --> 51:51.896
- It's just hard.
- Look.

51:51.965 --> 51:55.344
I loved Wayne too,
so of course I felt guilty

51:55.413 --> 51:58.931
when I started having feelings
for you after he passed,

51:59.000 --> 52:00.620
but it was years later.

52:00.689 --> 52:02.241
I only ever wanted
to help you through it--

52:02.310 --> 52:04.172
- And you did help me.

52:04.241 --> 52:05.896
And I...

52:05.965 --> 52:09.517
I realize it was 15 years ago
since he died,

52:09.586 --> 52:14.413
but it feels like yesterday.

52:14.482 --> 52:17.379
I don't know.
I just...

52:17.448 --> 52:19.379
puts me in a dark place.

52:19.448 --> 52:21.655
- Of course.
I get it.

52:21.724 --> 52:24.448
It happened to my Clara too,
you know?

52:24.517 --> 52:28.172
But we can't suffer alone
forever either.

52:28.241 --> 52:30.793
I mean, Wayne would've
wanted you to be happy again.

52:33.034 --> 52:35.655
- Oh.
- So great to see you.

52:35.724 --> 52:38.241
Such a lovely call the
other day about the ranch too.

52:38.310 --> 52:40.586
You know, I am just so excited
about the idea

52:40.655 --> 52:42.241
of being your realtor.

52:42.310 --> 52:44.448
- Oh, well, thank you, Suzanne.

52:44.517 --> 52:46.896
- I do wanna talk about
the asking price, though,

52:46.965 --> 52:48.275
as it's a bit steep.

52:48.344 --> 52:50.344
Maybe we could throw a horse
into the offer

52:50.413 --> 52:51.965
to sweeten the deal.
- Oh, uh--

52:52.034 --> 52:53.586
- Actually,
I'm so sorry to interrupt,

52:53.655 --> 52:56.275
but I think we might
already have our buyer.

52:56.344 --> 52:58.724
Yeah, uh, my boss.

52:58.793 --> 53:00.379
He's got this whole
race track idea

53:00.448 --> 53:01.758
and a angel investor

53:01.827 --> 53:04.137
who's willing to pay double
what it's worth.

53:04.206 --> 53:06.931
So thank you so much.
- Wow.

53:07.000 --> 53:08.724
Really, Wyatt?

53:14.137 --> 53:17.241
- Merry Christmas.

53:17.310 --> 53:19.689
- Hey.
- Hey, Ma.

53:19.758 --> 53:21.517
Need a hand?
- Oh, that's sweet.

53:21.586 --> 53:23.000
But I'm fine.

53:23.068 --> 53:25.551
- Now who wants to go on
a winter wonderland adventure?

53:25.620 --> 53:27.379
- I do.
- Yay!

53:31.379 --> 53:33.896
- So, uh,

53:33.965 --> 53:35.793
you and Heath, huh?

53:35.862 --> 53:37.862
- What about me and Heath?
- Oh, please.

53:37.931 --> 53:40.310
A mother always knows.
- Okay.

53:40.379 --> 53:42.034
Well, what about
you and Carlos?

53:42.103 --> 53:44.448
I saw the two of you talking
the other night,

53:44.517 --> 53:47.862
and then dancing
all slow and dreamy-like.

53:47.931 --> 53:49.724
- It was just one dance,

53:49.793 --> 53:53.000
and, you know, I got
to ask him about his lot,

53:53.068 --> 53:55.413
and that's all.

53:55.482 --> 53:57.896
- Uh-huh, keep your secrets.

53:57.965 --> 53:59.551
I'll be inside working
if you need me.

53:59.620 --> 54:02.172
I'm still trying to get
this promotion over here.

54:02.241 --> 54:06.310
Gotta finish the proposal
and get this place sold.

54:06.379 --> 54:07.689
- [sighs]

54:07.758 --> 54:10.758
Does it have to be
a race track?

54:10.827 --> 54:13.103
- Unless you can come up
with a better idea,

54:13.172 --> 54:14.758
find me a richer investor.

54:14.827 --> 54:16.620
- [sighs]
Oh.

54:16.689 --> 54:19.620
[mellow music]

54:19.689 --> 54:25.517
♪ ♪

54:25.586 --> 54:27.448
- Looks like someone had fun

54:27.517 --> 54:29.137
dancing with Carlos
the other night.

54:29.206 --> 54:31.655
- [chuckles]
You sound like Wyatt.

54:31.724 --> 54:34.655
It was fine.

54:34.724 --> 54:38.103
- I'm just saying I haven't
seen you smile like that

54:38.172 --> 54:40.206
in such a long time.

54:40.275 --> 54:44.034
- Well, I'm happy
because Wyatt's home.

54:44.103 --> 54:48.000
I did tell Carlos that
we were selling the ranch

54:48.068 --> 54:50.000
and he seemed really sad.

54:50.068 --> 54:52.965
- You know, we could still save
this ranch if you wanted to.

54:53.034 --> 54:55.310
We just need
a little bit of faith.

54:55.379 --> 54:58.000
And one big idea.

54:58.068 --> 54:59.965
- Do you have any better ideas
than some big,

55:00.034 --> 55:02.310
fancy moneymaking race track?

55:02.379 --> 55:03.827
- Well, I could keep
going to church

55:03.896 --> 55:05.344
and standing up
screaming on chairs

55:05.413 --> 55:07.482
to help keep
bringing in the locals.

55:07.551 --> 55:09.724
- [laughs]
Wyatt's probably right.

55:09.793 --> 55:12.172
He always is.
He's like his father that way.

55:12.241 --> 55:14.827
Me, I hold onto things
too long.

55:14.896 --> 55:17.379
Get too close to them.
- And what's wrong with that?

55:17.448 --> 55:20.655
- Well, apparently that's
how you end up old and alone.

55:20.724 --> 55:24.172
- [scoffs] I'm not so convinced
that Wyatt's dealt with

55:24.241 --> 55:26.241
Wayne's passing
in such a healthy way either.

55:26.310 --> 55:28.448
I think he brushes things
under the rug sometimes

55:28.517 --> 55:31.862
because it's easier
than dealing with the pain.

55:31.931 --> 55:34.344
And he's doing the same
with the ranch now.

55:34.413 --> 55:37.206
- He gets that from me.

55:37.275 --> 55:40.172
But regardless, he's right.

55:40.241 --> 55:42.241
The ranch won't survive
like this.

55:42.310 --> 55:45.965
- Like I said,
one good idea.

55:46.034 --> 55:48.034
- You mean like the date
you planned for my son

55:48.103 --> 55:50.241
down by the stables tonight?

55:50.310 --> 55:52.000
I snuck down there.

55:52.068 --> 55:54.275
I saw what you were up to
all day.

55:54.344 --> 55:57.724
- Well, he covered and saved
your dying hydrangeas

55:57.793 --> 55:59.862
from a cold and bitter winter.

55:59.931 --> 56:02.206
He can't be a total loss.
- [laughs]

56:02.275 --> 56:04.241
No, he's not.

56:04.310 --> 56:05.793
- Do you mind?

56:05.862 --> 56:07.724
Me taking out your son?

56:07.793 --> 56:11.448
- Oh, honey,
there is no one I would rather.

56:14.931 --> 56:16.827
- Hey.

56:16.896 --> 56:18.758
Dinner's almost ready.
You hungry?

56:18.827 --> 56:20.275
- I'll just be a few minutes.

56:20.344 --> 56:23.896
This stupid graphics program
is throwing me for a loop.

56:23.965 --> 56:26.413
- Graphic design?
- Mm-hmm.

56:26.482 --> 56:27.724
- That was my major.

56:27.793 --> 56:29.241
- Oh.

56:32.655 --> 56:35.275
What is it?
- [stammers]

56:35.344 --> 56:36.827
It's the proposal
for the race track

56:36.896 --> 56:38.517
to help sell to my boss' buyer.

56:38.586 --> 56:41.793
- Oh.
And you want my help on this?

56:41.862 --> 56:45.000
- I didn't ask for it.

56:45.068 --> 56:48.517
- Fine, but I'm only doing it
because it's you

56:48.586 --> 56:52.068
and because it seems like
we have no other choice.

56:57.448 --> 56:59.517
Let's see.

56:59.586 --> 57:02.379
What is this?

57:05.344 --> 57:09.206
[gentle music]

57:09.275 --> 57:11.275
Well, maybe your angel investor
would want

57:11.344 --> 57:14.206
a full-time winter wonderland

57:14.275 --> 57:16.586
for every season?

57:16.655 --> 57:18.517
- Maybe.

57:18.586 --> 57:20.137
- [sighs]

57:20.206 --> 57:23.448
No horse riding camp?

57:23.517 --> 57:25.758
I mean, this plan
is not very good.

57:28.103 --> 57:29.965
You talk to Blake about

57:30.034 --> 57:32.551
where we can place Nutmeg
once we've sold?

57:32.620 --> 57:35.344
- I haven't even thought about
where I'm gonna put Dasher.

57:35.413 --> 57:37.068
- I feel like he and Snow
should stay together

57:37.137 --> 57:39.000
if we can figure it out.

57:39.068 --> 57:42.931
Unless we can figure out a way
to save this place, you and me.

57:43.000 --> 57:45.931
- Mm, and how do you propose
to do that?

57:46.000 --> 57:49.724
- Well, he says
we just need one good idea.

57:49.793 --> 57:53.896
- Or maybe a few in this case.

57:53.965 --> 57:57.068
Oh, I meant to ask you,
where'd you find Snowbelle?

57:57.137 --> 57:59.000
Draft white mares are hard
to come by.

57:59.068 --> 58:01.310
- I started taking riding
lessons in this little place

58:01.379 --> 58:03.724
outside of Denver
when I was about 12.

58:03.793 --> 58:05.551
It just became a thing
I love to do,

58:05.620 --> 58:09.379
even more than hanging out
with my own friends.

58:09.448 --> 58:11.896
- I remember the feeling.

58:11.965 --> 58:13.551
Drink up.

58:13.620 --> 58:15.758
Y'all.
- [chuckles]

58:17.793 --> 58:19.862
[bird hoots]

58:19.931 --> 58:21.620
- What's the rush?

58:21.689 --> 58:23.724
Why are we out so late?
It's freezing.

58:23.793 --> 58:26.241
- It's a surprise.
- Ah.

58:28.172 --> 58:29.793
Hold up.

58:36.379 --> 58:38.275
When did you...

58:43.206 --> 58:50.206
♪ ♪

58:52.620 --> 58:54.655
This is incredible.

58:57.517 --> 59:00.551
- Blake said you never
got to dance with a boy,

59:00.620 --> 59:04.586
and you never asked me
to dance, so...

59:05.862 --> 59:08.344
- [chuckles]
- I'm asking you.

59:10.620 --> 59:14.172
- [stammers, sighs]

59:22.689 --> 59:24.413
[Kacey Musgraves'
"Oh, What a World" playing]

59:24.482 --> 59:27.172
- ♪ Northern lights ♪

59:27.241 --> 59:29.758
♪ In our skies ♪

59:29.827 --> 59:32.344
♪ Plants that grow and ♪

59:32.413 --> 59:35.482
♪ Open your mind ♪
- [laughs]

59:35.551 --> 59:37.758
- Come on, come on.
- I'm gonna go get some punch.

59:37.827 --> 59:40.000
- Come on.
- You start.

59:40.068 --> 59:42.448
- ♪ How we all got here ♪

59:42.517 --> 59:46.551
♪ Nobody knows ♪

59:46.620 --> 59:48.758
♪ These are real things ♪

59:48.827 --> 59:51.689
♪ ♪

59:51.758 --> 59:53.620
♪ These are real things ♪

59:53.689 --> 59:56.034
♪ Oh, what a world ♪

59:56.103 --> 59:58.689
♪ Don't wanna leave ♪

59:58.758 --> 1:00:02.344
♪ All kinds of magic
all around us ♪

1:00:02.413 --> 1:00:04.103
♪ It's hard to believe ♪

1:00:04.172 --> 1:00:06.344
♪ Thank God it's not ♪

1:00:06.413 --> 1:00:09.172
♪ Too good to be true ♪

1:00:09.241 --> 1:00:10.655
♪ Oh, what a world ♪

1:00:10.724 --> 1:00:14.103
[both chuckle]

1:00:14.172 --> 1:00:17.275
♪ And then there is you ♪

1:00:17.344 --> 1:00:24.344
♪ ♪

1:00:25.551 --> 1:00:30.896
♪ And then there is you ♪

1:00:30.965 --> 1:00:37.448
♪ ♪

1:00:37.517 --> 1:00:39.448
- Your heart's beating
really fast.

1:00:39.517 --> 1:00:42.137
♪ ♪

1:00:42.206 --> 1:00:44.448
- That's on you.

1:00:51.137 --> 1:00:54.000
[whimsical music]

1:00:54.068 --> 1:00:57.655
♪ ♪

1:00:57.724 --> 1:01:00.172
- ♪ Christmas eve ♪

1:01:00.241 --> 1:01:03.965
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

1:01:06.310 --> 1:01:08.034
Thank you.

1:01:08.103 --> 1:01:09.689
- [chuckles]
You're welcome.

1:01:09.758 --> 1:01:15.965
♪ ♪

1:01:16.034 --> 1:01:19.965
- So what is it that you love
so much about Christmas?

1:01:20.034 --> 1:01:21.827
- If we treated
every day of the year

1:01:21.896 --> 1:01:26.517
with the kind of love,
and goodness, magic--

1:01:26.586 --> 1:01:28.586
the kind you only see
at Christmastime,

1:01:28.655 --> 1:01:31.310
where would the world be?

1:01:31.379 --> 1:01:33.793
- I like that.

1:01:33.862 --> 1:01:36.931
Where to next?
- Anywhere you wanna go.

1:01:37.000 --> 1:01:38.517
I'm in.

1:01:38.586 --> 1:01:45.620
♪ ♪

1:01:49.620 --> 1:01:52.275
[owl hooting]

1:01:59.275 --> 1:02:02.241
- This is bringing back
so many memories.

1:02:02.310 --> 1:02:04.758
I remember when Dad got
that Santa back there.

1:02:04.827 --> 1:02:08.172
[laughs]
He was so proud.

1:02:08.241 --> 1:02:12.482
- May I ask, um, is that why
you stopped doing the rides?

1:02:12.551 --> 1:02:14.310
Your father?

1:02:16.482 --> 1:02:18.965
- Yeah.

1:02:19.034 --> 1:02:22.413
Yeah, after he passed,
it just hurt too much.

1:02:22.482 --> 1:02:26.206
It was always something
we did together.

1:02:26.275 --> 1:02:28.241
But in spite of it all,

1:02:28.310 --> 1:02:30.620
I'm still really
gonna miss this place.

1:02:30.689 --> 1:02:35.551
- Hey, this place had
a really good run, didn't it?

1:02:35.620 --> 1:02:39.206
And you guys did make
something special here.

1:02:39.275 --> 1:02:42.448
- Yeah.
Yeah, we sure did.

1:02:42.517 --> 1:02:45.241
I'd almost forgotten.
[sighs]

1:02:45.310 --> 1:02:47.068
I thought I was choosing
greener pastures

1:02:47.137 --> 1:02:50.482
when I left Harmony Springs.

1:02:50.551 --> 1:02:52.482
Now, I'm not so sure.

1:02:52.551 --> 1:02:57.241
- It's not always about
finding a greener pasture.

1:02:57.310 --> 1:02:59.206
Sometimes you just have
to find a way

1:02:59.275 --> 1:03:02.034
to farm the pastures
you already have.

1:03:05.206 --> 1:03:07.379
- How are you feeling
about all this?

1:03:07.448 --> 1:03:10.448
- I'm worried about Snowbelle
and what's next.

1:03:10.517 --> 1:03:14.413
♪ ♪

1:03:14.482 --> 1:03:16.965
- [sighs]
Maybe you won't have to.

1:03:17.034 --> 1:03:20.000
[gentle music]

1:03:20.068 --> 1:03:27.068
♪ ♪

1:03:41.000 --> 1:03:44.827
- So, um, what was this for?

1:03:44.896 --> 1:03:47.344
- It's for Heath,
and he's gonna love it.

1:03:47.413 --> 1:03:49.758
- I have never seen you
do anything like this

1:03:49.827 --> 1:03:51.482
for a guy before.

1:03:51.551 --> 1:03:53.896
- You're not in New York.
You don't have a spy cam.

1:03:53.965 --> 1:03:57.103
You don't know what I do
for my dates and my boyfriends.

1:03:57.172 --> 1:03:58.827
- Well, have you done anything
like this?

1:03:58.896 --> 1:04:00.931
- [sighs]
- I'm just saying.

1:04:01.000 --> 1:04:02.379
I think it's wonderful,

1:04:02.448 --> 1:04:05.172
and what he did for you
last night was so special.

1:04:05.241 --> 1:04:07.931
- All right, don't go
all maudlin on me, Mother.

1:04:08.000 --> 1:04:10.172
- So what are you gonna do
after the holidays

1:04:10.241 --> 1:04:11.862
when you have to go?

1:04:11.931 --> 1:04:13.034
- I don't know.

1:04:13.103 --> 1:04:15.379
I haven't given it
much thought.

1:04:15.448 --> 1:04:17.758
- Wy, can I ask you something?
- Mm-hmm.

1:04:19.206 --> 1:04:22.137
- Why did it take you so long
to come home?

1:04:22.206 --> 1:04:24.793
I mean, I'm not angry,
or hurt, or anything.

1:04:24.862 --> 1:04:26.862
It's just...

1:04:26.931 --> 1:04:29.000
it was really hard

1:04:29.068 --> 1:04:32.517
not having you here
for so long.

1:04:32.586 --> 1:04:36.896
And I just wondered
if I had done anything,

1:04:36.965 --> 1:04:39.241
or if it's because I'm sad--

1:04:39.310 --> 1:04:42.724
- No, no, no, please don't ever
think like that, Mom.

1:04:42.793 --> 1:04:44.206
It wasn't you.

1:04:44.275 --> 1:04:46.137
I'm so sorry that it took me
so long to come home.

1:04:46.206 --> 1:04:47.965
It just always felt...

1:04:48.034 --> 1:04:51.896
heavier than the alternative,
you know?

1:04:51.965 --> 1:04:53.827
Being back,

1:04:53.896 --> 1:04:57.413
I--I just see Dad
wherever I look.

1:05:00.275 --> 1:05:02.000
I just really still miss him,
you know?

1:05:02.068 --> 1:05:05.758
- Yeah.
I get that, sweetheart.

1:05:05.827 --> 1:05:08.689
He was one of a kind.

1:05:08.758 --> 1:05:10.275
I don't think we ever
get over the loss

1:05:10.344 --> 1:05:11.931
of someone that we love.

1:05:12.000 --> 1:05:15.172
I just think we have
to learn to...

1:05:15.241 --> 1:05:18.724
lean a little harder on
the ones that are still here.

1:05:18.793 --> 1:05:21.965
- Yeah, you're right.

1:05:24.172 --> 1:05:26.413
- [sighs]
I love you.

1:05:26.482 --> 1:05:28.413
- I love you too, Mom.

1:05:28.482 --> 1:05:30.172
- [chuckles]

1:05:30.241 --> 1:05:32.310
- And hey, I will never
do that to you again, okay?

1:05:32.379 --> 1:05:34.206
I promise.

1:05:34.275 --> 1:05:37.172
- Okay.
[chuckles]

1:05:42.758 --> 1:05:45.793
[animals chirping]

1:05:48.275 --> 1:05:52.586
- Hey, Blake, do you wanna
grab something to eat?

1:05:52.655 --> 1:05:55.068
- Yeah, sure.

1:06:00.275 --> 1:06:03.689
[indistinct chatter]
- Ooh, yeah, I do, yeah.

1:06:03.758 --> 1:06:06.344
- Well, it's not exactly the
cheap champagne that you like,

1:06:06.413 --> 1:06:09.310
but we do have a copy
of "It's a Wonderful Life."

1:06:09.379 --> 1:06:13.068
- Whoo!
[laughs]

1:06:13.137 --> 1:06:14.965
- Cheers.
Cheers, cheers, cheers.

1:06:15.034 --> 1:06:16.965
- Aw.
- Mmm.

1:06:17.034 --> 1:06:20.413
- Mmm.
Hmm, not bad.

1:06:20.482 --> 1:06:23.482
- This bison chili
is just amazing, Deb.

1:06:23.551 --> 1:06:26.827
I'm telling you really...
- Oh, thank you.

1:06:26.896 --> 1:06:29.068
But I didn't make it.
Wyatt did.

1:06:29.137 --> 1:06:31.413
It's his father's recipe.
- What?

1:06:31.482 --> 1:06:35.620
- See, I can do some
Christmas magic of my own.

1:06:35.689 --> 1:06:37.827
- So, um,

1:06:37.896 --> 1:06:41.241
what is everybody's
Christmas wish?

1:06:41.310 --> 1:06:43.413
Blake, you go.
- Me?

1:06:43.482 --> 1:06:46.931
Okay, well,

1:06:47.000 --> 1:06:49.448
good news on Sam's sabbatical
from Doctors Without Borders

1:06:49.517 --> 1:06:51.068
would be really nice.
- Mm-hmm.

1:06:51.137 --> 1:06:52.689
- You know, this was the year
we were supposed

1:06:52.758 --> 1:06:53.862
to start trying for a baby,

1:06:53.931 --> 1:06:55.517
and it's already
the end of the year,

1:06:55.586 --> 1:06:58.172
and I don't know when
he's gonna be home next, so...

1:06:58.241 --> 1:07:01.034
- Well, we are just
gonna have to remind Santa

1:07:01.103 --> 1:07:03.000
to make a quick pit stop
at the medical center

1:07:03.068 --> 1:07:04.241
down on the Capes.

1:07:04.310 --> 1:07:07.551
- Thanks.
You go, Deb.

1:07:07.620 --> 1:07:10.137
- Well, I already got
my Christmas wish.

1:07:10.206 --> 1:07:11.827
Wyatt's home.
- Aw.

1:07:11.896 --> 1:07:13.586
[laughter]

1:07:16.793 --> 1:07:19.827
- And you, Wyatt?
- Oh, well, that's tough.

1:07:19.896 --> 1:07:22.551
It's a tossup between
world peace and a new car.

1:07:22.620 --> 1:07:23.724
- Boo.
- Kidding.

1:07:23.793 --> 1:07:25.034
I'm kidding.
I'm half-kidding.

1:07:25.103 --> 1:07:27.000
I actually really do want
the new Mercedes GT,

1:07:27.068 --> 1:07:30.172
but it's a hybrid,
so y'all can just relax.

1:07:30.241 --> 1:07:33.862
What about you, Mr. Judgmental?

1:07:33.931 --> 1:07:36.034
- Me?
Uh...

1:07:38.448 --> 1:07:42.310
I wish we didn't have
to leave the ranch,

1:07:42.379 --> 1:07:43.758
Snowbelle's home.

1:07:43.827 --> 1:07:45.551
- Hmm.

1:07:45.620 --> 1:07:49.517
- Well, what if you were to...

1:07:49.586 --> 1:07:51.931
board her at a cute little
ranch in Upstate New York?

1:07:52.000 --> 1:07:53.344
You know,
give the East Coast a try?

1:07:53.413 --> 1:07:55.896
You're so good with
your Photoshop and graphics.

1:07:55.965 --> 1:08:00.068
I'm sure I can get you a job
in our marketing department.

1:08:00.137 --> 1:08:03.103
- Are you serious?
- Yeah, I mean, why not?

1:08:03.172 --> 1:08:05.137
I mean, it might
be entry level, but--

1:08:05.206 --> 1:08:08.586
- No, I mean...

1:08:08.655 --> 1:08:11.586
you can't be serious.

1:08:11.655 --> 1:08:13.379
You think I wanna
abandon my horse

1:08:13.448 --> 1:08:16.620
and just come and live
in New York with you?

1:08:16.689 --> 1:08:18.862
Just leave everything
I built here

1:08:18.931 --> 1:08:21.379
in the off chance
that you might,

1:08:21.448 --> 1:08:25.033
or might not, dump me
like all the other guys?

1:08:25.103 --> 1:08:27.344
- I was offering
a possibility.

1:08:27.413 --> 1:08:29.689
- Look,

1:08:29.758 --> 1:08:32.344
you know how much
I hate moving around.

1:08:32.413 --> 1:08:34.724
I already told you that.
- Mm-hmm.

1:08:34.792 --> 1:08:38.792
- And I know that you're used
to focusing on yourself

1:08:38.862 --> 1:08:41.862
before your commitments
to your family,

1:08:41.931 --> 1:08:44.033
your ranch, your mom,

1:08:44.103 --> 1:08:46.689
your friends, your horse,

1:08:46.758 --> 1:08:51.000
but that's just not me,
and that's just not an option.

1:08:52.585 --> 1:08:54.206
- I'm sorry.
[chuckles]

1:08:54.274 --> 1:08:56.827
I guess I'm not perfectly clear
on what your intentions are

1:08:56.896 --> 1:08:58.896
to do here because

1:08:58.965 --> 1:09:01.274
this place isn't gonna be
around much longer,

1:09:01.344 --> 1:09:03.068
and that includes your home,

1:09:03.137 --> 1:09:05.792
and the stable
where your horse lives, so--

1:09:05.862 --> 1:09:07.724
- Yeah, that's thanks to you

1:09:07.792 --> 1:09:10.896
because you cannot think
of anyone but yourself.

1:09:10.965 --> 1:09:13.309
- Okay, guys, can you just--
- No, no, it's fine.

1:09:13.379 --> 1:09:15.068
It's fine, he's fine.
Keep going, Heath.

1:09:15.137 --> 1:09:17.344
You're on a roll making me out
to be the bad guy.

1:09:17.413 --> 1:09:19.103
You know what?
You're right.

1:09:19.172 --> 1:09:21.379
And I'm used to it.
- That's not true, Wyatt.

1:09:21.448 --> 1:09:24.000
- No, it is.
He's right.

1:09:24.068 --> 1:09:27.172
And the truth is, I do care
more about my promotion

1:09:27.241 --> 1:09:29.965
to senior VP than this ranch,
and that is because

1:09:30.033 --> 1:09:31.758
I have worked
for everything that I have

1:09:31.827 --> 1:09:33.792
and I will not apologize
for it.

1:09:33.862 --> 1:09:35.448
And I happen to think
it's a whole lot better

1:09:35.517 --> 1:09:37.103
than just sitting around here
in hibernation

1:09:37.172 --> 1:09:39.792
like the rest of you
just pretending to be happy

1:09:39.862 --> 1:09:41.413
when none of you actually are.

1:09:41.482 --> 1:09:44.033
- All right, that's not fair.
We're doing just fine.

1:09:44.103 --> 1:09:45.620
- Okay, you're not just
waiting around all day

1:09:45.689 --> 1:09:47.309
for Sam to come home?

1:09:47.379 --> 1:09:49.758
And Mom, you can't even admit
that you're in love with Carlos

1:09:49.827 --> 1:09:52.413
no matter how hard
he tries to be with you.

1:09:52.482 --> 1:09:54.482
And yeah.
Sure, whatever.

1:09:54.550 --> 1:09:58.033
I date around a lot,
but look at you, Heath.

1:09:58.103 --> 1:10:00.344
You're not even awake enough
to put yourself out there

1:10:00.413 --> 1:10:02.620
to take a chance on someone.

1:10:02.689 --> 1:10:04.655
You'd rather just hide out here
with the horses

1:10:04.724 --> 1:10:06.655
where it's safe.

1:10:06.724 --> 1:10:09.862
It's sad.

1:10:09.931 --> 1:10:12.344
- [scoffs]
Wow.

1:10:14.585 --> 1:10:17.482
Yeah, well,

1:10:17.550 --> 1:10:20.344
you are right about one thing.

1:10:20.413 --> 1:10:23.758
I was ready
to take a chance.

1:10:26.000 --> 1:10:28.206
That was a mistake.

1:10:28.274 --> 1:10:31.379
Excuse me.
Sorry.

1:10:35.172 --> 1:10:37.724
- [sniffling]

1:10:40.309 --> 1:10:43.274
I'm sorry, Mom.
That was out of line.

1:10:43.344 --> 1:10:46.792
- Yeah.
[sighs]

1:10:46.862 --> 1:10:49.792
Sweetheart,
I know you didn't mean it

1:10:49.862 --> 1:10:53.482
and I know that all of this

1:10:53.550 --> 1:10:55.896
has been a lot of stress
on you too.

1:10:55.965 --> 1:10:57.344
- I'm sorry, Blake.

1:10:59.827 --> 1:11:02.827
- Don't apologize to me, Wy.

1:11:02.896 --> 1:11:04.274
Go to him.

1:11:04.344 --> 1:11:06.620
- [stammers, sighs]
No.

1:11:06.689 --> 1:11:08.413
I--I have to go.
I--

1:11:08.482 --> 1:11:11.585
- Wyatt.
- I can't be here anymore.

1:11:11.655 --> 1:11:13.862
- [groans]
Oh, God.

1:11:15.758 --> 1:11:18.274
Well, that did not go
as planned.

1:11:21.413 --> 1:11:22.585
- [sighs]

1:11:27.896 --> 1:11:29.689
- Hey.

1:11:29.758 --> 1:11:32.413
Wyatt, it's almost Christmas.

1:11:32.482 --> 1:11:33.655
I know you're hurt,

1:11:33.724 --> 1:11:36.862
but can't you stay
until after the holiday?

1:11:36.931 --> 1:11:40.172
- Yeah, I gotta get back
and get this whole proposal

1:11:40.241 --> 1:11:42.655
wrapped up
before the new year, so--

1:11:42.724 --> 1:11:44.137
- What about Heath?

1:11:44.206 --> 1:11:45.550
If you go,
it's gonna break his heart.

1:11:45.620 --> 1:11:48.448
- Isn't that exactly
what he set me up to do?

1:11:48.517 --> 1:11:51.550
To disappoint him?

1:11:51.620 --> 1:11:54.517
Anyway, he doesn't wanna
leave his home

1:11:54.585 --> 1:11:56.689
and I gotta stop pretending
that this is still mine,

1:11:56.758 --> 1:11:59.517
so it's done.

1:11:59.585 --> 1:12:01.448
- Hey.

1:12:03.448 --> 1:12:05.758
I'm gonna miss you, Sugar Cube.

1:12:05.827 --> 1:12:08.275
- Yeah.
You too, Snow Pea.

1:12:08.344 --> 1:12:11.275
["Winter Song" playing]

1:12:11.344 --> 1:12:18.344
♪ ♪

1:12:28.482 --> 1:12:32.137
- ♪ This is my winter song
to you ♪

1:12:32.206 --> 1:12:35.241
♪ The storm is coming soon ♪

1:12:35.309 --> 1:12:38.931
♪ ♪

1:12:39.000 --> 1:12:40.379
- [sighing]

1:12:40.448 --> 1:12:44.103
- ♪ My voice,
a beacon in the night ♪

1:12:44.172 --> 1:12:47.068
♪ My words will be
your light ♪

1:12:47.137 --> 1:12:50.724
♪ To carry you to me ♪

1:12:50.793 --> 1:12:53.689
♪ Is love alive? ♪

1:12:53.758 --> 1:12:57.241
♪ Is love alive? ♪

