1:14:31.241 --> 1:14:35.758
♪ Is love alive?
Is love alive? ♪

1:14:44.931 --> 1:14:48.550
- Yeah, me too.

1:14:48.620 --> 1:14:51.068
I'm sorry, ol' boy.
[sighs]

1:14:51.137 --> 1:14:54.344
I'll be back soon, okay?

1:14:54.413 --> 1:14:56.413
This time, I promise.

1:15:03.344 --> 1:15:05.000
[sighs]

1:15:10.275 --> 1:15:11.620
Well, I finally
got up the courage

1:15:11.689 --> 1:15:13.309
to visit Dad's thinking spot.

1:15:13.379 --> 1:15:17.172
- Aw.
- Quick hello and goodbye.

1:15:17.241 --> 1:15:20.241
It was nice.
- I'm so glad, Wyatt.

1:15:20.309 --> 1:15:22.103
I, um--

1:15:22.172 --> 1:15:25.793
we wish you wouldn't leave.

1:15:25.862 --> 1:15:28.275
- Yeah, well,
I really gotta get back

1:15:28.344 --> 1:15:30.448
and meet with the investors
about this place,

1:15:30.517 --> 1:15:32.827
but I promise I will be back
after the new year

1:15:32.896 --> 1:15:34.309
to help you
with the transition, okay?

1:15:34.379 --> 1:15:35.724
- You can't always leave

1:15:35.793 --> 1:15:38.068
because it's lighter
than the alternative, Wyatt.

1:15:38.137 --> 1:15:40.137
[sighs]

1:15:40.206 --> 1:15:42.309
- What would Carlos say
about that, Ma?

1:15:42.379 --> 1:15:45.931
- You're right, and
you deal with life like me.

1:15:46.000 --> 1:15:47.309
Look how many years
I've wasted.

1:15:47.379 --> 1:15:49.275
How many years
are you gonna waste?

1:15:49.344 --> 1:15:51.965
Your dad was
the complete opposite.

1:15:52.034 --> 1:15:55.241
No matter what life threw
at him, he always chose love,

1:15:55.309 --> 1:15:59.103
and that's what I loved
about him so much.

1:15:59.172 --> 1:16:02.137
That's why, you know,
it's hard to let go.

1:16:02.206 --> 1:16:04.137
I feel like
I'm giving up on him.

1:16:04.206 --> 1:16:06.448
- I'm not like Dad.

1:16:06.517 --> 1:16:08.965
I might have his drive,
but I don't have his heart.

1:16:09.034 --> 1:16:12.965
- Well, Heath has his heart.
It's big, and it's good.

1:16:13.034 --> 1:16:15.689
And he needs someone
to protect it.

1:16:15.758 --> 1:16:19.482
And that's you.
- You're wrong, Mom.

1:16:19.550 --> 1:16:21.309
And I'm not gonna let Heath
waste what he has

1:16:21.379 --> 1:16:22.517
on someone like me.

1:16:22.585 --> 1:16:25.172
- [scoffs]
Come here.

1:16:25.241 --> 1:16:26.793
[both sigh]

1:16:26.862 --> 1:16:29.793
[gentle music]

1:16:29.862 --> 1:16:33.034
♪ ♪

1:16:33.103 --> 1:16:35.896
- I'll call you as soon
as I get back home, okay?

1:16:35.965 --> 1:16:37.655
I love you, Ma.

1:16:37.724 --> 1:16:39.482
- I love you.

1:16:42.379 --> 1:16:44.103
- And will you call him,
please?

1:16:44.172 --> 1:16:46.448
- [chuckles]
- It's time.

1:16:46.517 --> 1:16:49.758
- Yeah.
Merry Christmas.

1:16:49.827 --> 1:16:51.689
- Merry Christmas.

1:16:56.000 --> 1:16:57.413
- [sighs]

1:17:05.068 --> 1:17:12.068
♪ ♪

1:17:18.344 --> 1:17:21.068
Hey.
- Hey.

1:17:21.137 --> 1:17:23.482
You want some coffee?
- Sure.

1:17:25.206 --> 1:17:27.309
You going somewhere?

1:17:27.379 --> 1:17:29.965
- I'm gonna stay
with Blake tonight

1:17:30.034 --> 1:17:32.137
since her husband isn't
gonna be back for Christmas,

1:17:32.206 --> 1:17:34.413
but I'll be back
tomorrow morning

1:17:34.482 --> 1:17:36.724
for the sleigh ride's last day.

1:17:36.793 --> 1:17:38.965
- You know I don't wanna close
any more than you do.

1:17:39.034 --> 1:17:40.827
- Of course I do.
- Who knows?

1:17:40.896 --> 1:17:43.793
Maybe I'll come up
with one great idea.

1:17:43.862 --> 1:17:46.965
- Or maybe a few.
- [chuckles]

1:17:47.034 --> 1:17:49.724
Hey, Heath,

1:17:49.793 --> 1:17:51.931
I wanted to tell you.

1:17:52.000 --> 1:17:53.965
[chuckles]

1:17:54.034 --> 1:17:58.068
I wanted you to know
that no matter what happens--

1:17:58.137 --> 1:18:01.137
I mean, I know I could never
take your mother's place,

1:18:01.206 --> 1:18:05.448
but I do love you like a son.

1:18:05.517 --> 1:18:07.793
- [sighs]
Deb.

1:18:07.862 --> 1:18:11.689
Oh, I love you too.
So much.

1:18:14.550 --> 1:18:17.068
Hey.

1:18:17.137 --> 1:18:21.275
You never mentioned Wyatt
was gay to me before now.

1:18:21.344 --> 1:18:23.103
Why was that?

1:18:23.172 --> 1:18:26.620
- Well, he's my son.
It doesn't define him.

1:18:26.689 --> 1:18:28.793
It doesn't define you.

1:18:28.862 --> 1:18:32.000
You're just two good people

1:18:32.068 --> 1:18:34.585
that I dreamed
might meet one day

1:18:34.655 --> 1:18:36.896
and hit it off.

1:18:36.965 --> 1:18:38.448
Love comes
at different times

1:18:38.517 --> 1:18:41.482
in different ways,
and you can't anticipate it

1:18:41.550 --> 1:18:44.965
because you never
see it coming.

1:18:45.034 --> 1:18:48.275
But if we find it,

1:18:48.344 --> 1:18:50.689
we better hold onto it.

1:19:00.448 --> 1:19:02.379
- Oh.

1:19:04.309 --> 1:19:05.862
[sighs]

1:19:10.517 --> 1:19:13.896
Hi, Carlos.
It's Deb.

1:19:13.965 --> 1:19:16.585
Oh, I'm fine.
Thanks.

1:19:16.655 --> 1:19:20.620
Um, listen...
[laughs]

1:19:20.689 --> 1:19:22.965
I was just wondering,

1:19:23.034 --> 1:19:26.931
are you doing anything
this evening?

1:19:27.000 --> 1:19:28.275
[chuckles]

1:19:34.344 --> 1:19:37.344
[indistinct PA announcements]

1:19:46.413 --> 1:19:49.620
- Hey, yeah, I should land
early tomorrow morning.

1:19:49.689 --> 1:19:52.137
- And you think we can
make this deal happen

1:19:52.206 --> 1:19:53.137
by the new year?

1:19:53.206 --> 1:19:55.000
- I am certainly gonna try.

1:19:55.068 --> 1:19:56.862
- You can do better than that.

1:19:56.931 --> 1:19:59.517
I just landed us
Ponderosa Organics, Wyatt.

1:19:59.585 --> 1:20:01.827
- I know, and I also understand

1:20:01.896 --> 1:20:04.309
that my entire promotion
depends

1:20:04.379 --> 1:20:08.172
on one very good idea,
one surefire sell.

1:20:08.241 --> 1:20:11.034
- Exactly.

1:20:11.103 --> 1:20:12.517
- What if it was more
than just one thing?

1:20:12.585 --> 1:20:14.827
- A race track
is what my buyer discussed.

1:20:14.896 --> 1:20:16.482
That's just one thing.
- Right.

1:20:16.550 --> 1:20:18.379
But what if
it wasn't your buyer?

1:20:18.448 --> 1:20:19.965
What if it was my buyer,
and I got him

1:20:20.034 --> 1:20:22.309
to sign off on an idea
that I just got right now?

1:20:22.379 --> 1:20:24.344
And what if--
just hear me out here--

1:20:24.413 --> 1:20:27.482
what if we're able to tie in
the new organics brand

1:20:27.550 --> 1:20:28.965
that you just bought out?

1:20:29.034 --> 1:20:31.758
- I'm listening.
It better be a big idea.

1:20:31.827 --> 1:20:33.793
And you still owe my buyer
a property west

1:20:33.862 --> 1:20:35.241
if that's the case.

1:20:35.309 --> 1:20:36.550
- Hugh, I love you.
Thank you, thank you.

1:20:36.620 --> 1:20:38.034
Thank you so much.

1:20:38.103 --> 1:20:40.137
Look, I gotta go, but I will
get you a new property

1:20:40.206 --> 1:20:42.068
as soon as I possibly can.

1:20:42.137 --> 1:20:44.689
- Wyatt, don't do
anything risky.

1:20:44.758 --> 1:20:46.724
- Me, risky?
No, never.

1:20:46.793 --> 1:20:50.172
I promise you, surefire sell.

1:20:50.241 --> 1:20:51.931
[sighs]
Oh, do me a favor.

1:20:52.000 --> 1:20:54.931
Will you send me Mariana from
PR's contact right now, please?

1:20:55.000 --> 1:20:57.620
- Fine, fine.
It's coming your way.

1:20:57.689 --> 1:21:00.103
- Merry Christmas, Hugh.

1:21:06.758 --> 1:21:07.931
- Hey.

1:21:10.413 --> 1:21:13.206
We could watch
"A Christmas Story."

1:21:13.275 --> 1:21:15.068
- [sighs]
Yeah.

1:21:16.931 --> 1:21:20.068
- We could make
Christmas cookies.

1:21:22.206 --> 1:21:25.655
Maybe we could just open
each other's gifts.

1:21:25.724 --> 1:21:26.965
Hmm?

1:21:27.034 --> 1:21:29.448
I see a smile.
Okay.

1:21:35.172 --> 1:21:38.550
- Whoa.
- [chuckles]

1:21:38.620 --> 1:21:41.517
- Let me guess.
A new pair of boots.

1:21:41.585 --> 1:21:44.241
- What, no.
I got that for you last year.

1:21:48.448 --> 1:21:50.620
[both laugh]

1:21:50.689 --> 1:21:52.344
And I got them for you
this year too

1:21:52.413 --> 1:21:55.379
because, well, you know,
you always need new boots.

1:21:55.448 --> 1:21:58.550
- Wow, these are
really incredible, Blake.

1:21:58.620 --> 1:22:01.655
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

1:22:01.724 --> 1:22:03.413
Wow.
- Okay, my turn.

1:22:03.482 --> 1:22:06.275
My turn.
[chuckles]

1:22:06.344 --> 1:22:08.517
Thanks.

1:22:13.413 --> 1:22:14.896
- [chuckles]

1:22:14.965 --> 1:22:16.137
- Heath.

1:22:18.517 --> 1:22:21.896
[sighs]
I'm not even pregnant yet.

1:22:21.965 --> 1:22:23.620
- But you will be.

1:22:23.689 --> 1:22:26.931
And I wanted to be the first
to get your little baby

1:22:27.000 --> 1:22:29.448
their first
gender neutral wardrobe.

1:22:29.517 --> 1:22:30.896
- Thank you.

1:22:32.965 --> 1:22:34.068
Oh, come here.

1:22:34.137 --> 1:22:36.000
- Love you.
- Love you.

1:22:38.620 --> 1:22:40.448
- [exhales]

1:22:43.309 --> 1:22:46.758
- Who could be here so late?
- I don't know.

1:22:46.827 --> 1:22:48.965
- Okay.

1:22:49.034 --> 1:22:51.965
[hopeful music]

1:22:52.034 --> 1:22:53.793
♪ ♪

1:22:53.862 --> 1:22:56.034
- Sam.

1:22:56.103 --> 1:22:58.034
Uh, what are you--

1:22:58.103 --> 1:23:00.034
- I just got my one-year
sabbatical approved

1:23:00.103 --> 1:23:03.344
starting January 1st.

1:23:03.413 --> 1:23:05.758
Merry Christmas, babe.
[both laugh]

1:23:08.379 --> 1:23:09.896
Hey.
- Hey.

1:23:11.896 --> 1:23:14.000
- Mom!

1:23:14.068 --> 1:23:15.241
- Wyatt.

1:23:17.620 --> 1:23:19.206
What are you doing here?

1:23:19.275 --> 1:23:21.379
- I think I may have figured
out a way to save the ranch.

1:23:21.448 --> 1:23:23.862
Well, a lot of ways,
but I'm gonna need your help.

1:23:23.931 --> 1:23:25.655
And yours.

1:23:25.724 --> 1:23:27.827
- Well, I guess
I'm glad I came.

1:23:27.896 --> 1:23:29.793
[both laugh]
- Wait, Carlos.

1:23:29.862 --> 1:23:32.517
You're here.
Well, well, well.

1:23:32.585 --> 1:23:35.068
We might just have
a merry Christmas after all.

1:23:35.137 --> 1:23:36.758
I guess I'll leave you to it.

1:23:39.724 --> 1:23:42.620
[hopeful music]

1:23:42.689 --> 1:23:46.689
♪ ♪

1:23:46.758 --> 1:23:50.620
- [gasps]
Heath, merry Christmas Eve.

1:23:50.689 --> 1:23:52.793
- What is all this?
- Pretty incredible, right?

1:23:52.862 --> 1:23:54.206
- Merry Christmas.
Your tickets.

1:23:54.275 --> 1:23:56.482
- It is incredible.
Deb.

1:23:56.550 --> 1:23:58.379
Where did all these people
come from?

1:23:58.448 --> 1:23:59.585
- They're here
for the carriage.

1:23:59.655 --> 1:24:01.068
Can you believe it?

1:24:01.137 --> 1:24:03.724
We have not had a turnout
like this in a dozen years.

1:24:03.793 --> 1:24:05.379
- But how?

1:24:05.448 --> 1:24:09.206
- Wyatt's boss had his PR gal
send out a social media blast

1:24:09.275 --> 1:24:11.275
to all the followers
of a little company

1:24:11.344 --> 1:24:15.206
you might have heard of,
Ponderosa Organics.

1:24:15.275 --> 1:24:17.448
- Ponderosa Organics,
but what do we have to do

1:24:17.517 --> 1:24:18.550
with Ponderosa Organics?

1:24:18.620 --> 1:24:19.896
- A lot now.

1:24:19.965 --> 1:24:21.379
Wyatt struck a deal
with them this morning

1:24:21.448 --> 1:24:23.793
to open their next organic farm

1:24:23.862 --> 1:24:26.758
right here
on our western expanse.

1:24:26.827 --> 1:24:29.241
- But what about
the horse race track?

1:24:29.309 --> 1:24:31.379
- The only horses that
you're gonna see on this ranch

1:24:31.448 --> 1:24:33.413
are ours.

1:24:33.482 --> 1:24:35.827
[chuckles]

1:24:35.896 --> 1:24:38.206
- All right, this one is
for you and this one is yours.

1:24:38.275 --> 1:24:40.000
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1:24:41.620 --> 1:24:43.758
- Sneaky you.

1:24:43.827 --> 1:24:46.000
I was wondering where you
disappeared to this morning.

1:24:46.068 --> 1:24:47.862
- Yeah, I got a little text
from Deb

1:24:47.931 --> 1:24:49.241
that you needed
some extra hands.

1:24:49.309 --> 1:24:51.172
- Yeah, here we go.

1:24:51.241 --> 1:24:53.862
We got fresh hot cocoa.
Real milk, or organic oat?

1:24:53.931 --> 1:24:56.309
We have both.
- I'll have milk.

1:24:56.379 --> 1:24:59.309
- I'll try the oat.
Thank you.

1:24:59.379 --> 1:25:00.517
- All right,
now who here is ready

1:25:00.585 --> 1:25:03.241
for a winter wonderland
adventure?

1:25:03.309 --> 1:25:04.655
[kids cheers]

1:25:04.724 --> 1:25:06.413
- Well, I say he makes
a mighty fine cowboy.

1:25:06.482 --> 1:25:09.241
- Sure does.

1:25:09.309 --> 1:25:12.585
Hey, we'll meet you
on the carriage.

1:25:12.655 --> 1:25:14.620
Snazzy.
- [chuckles]

1:25:20.827 --> 1:25:22.448
- What are you doing back here?

1:25:22.517 --> 1:25:25.655
I thought you'd be back
in New York at the office

1:25:25.724 --> 1:25:29.275
or out partying
in Fire Island by now.

1:25:29.344 --> 1:25:31.827
- I came back to say I'm sorry.

1:25:31.896 --> 1:25:35.103
And to thank you.
What I said was a lie.

1:25:35.172 --> 1:25:37.309
It wasn't any of you
who were in hibernation.

1:25:37.379 --> 1:25:39.517
It was me.

1:25:39.585 --> 1:25:42.689
I didn't even realize it
until I came back here.

1:25:42.758 --> 1:25:47.724
Until all these people I love
woke me up.

1:25:47.793 --> 1:25:50.758
Until you did.

1:25:50.827 --> 1:25:52.585
- And what is this about
you buying the ranch

1:25:52.655 --> 1:25:54.517
instead of your investor?

1:25:54.585 --> 1:25:57.517
- It now belongs to me
and one other investor.

1:25:57.585 --> 1:26:00.000
We're gonna split the farm
between Carlos' property

1:26:00.068 --> 1:26:03.758
and our south side,
so the horse land won't suffer.

1:26:03.827 --> 1:26:05.206
Well, a few acres
for sustainability,

1:26:05.275 --> 1:26:07.550
but the majority will remain--

1:26:07.620 --> 1:26:11.034
horses, stables, everything.

1:26:11.103 --> 1:26:12.931
- I'm still not moving
to Manhattan.

1:26:13.000 --> 1:26:15.758
- Good, that's a relief because
the way things are headed,

1:26:15.827 --> 1:26:18.379
Mom's gonna be retired
and married in no time

1:26:18.448 --> 1:26:20.517
and someone needs
to run this ranch,

1:26:20.585 --> 1:26:23.206
the horseback riding lessons,
and--oh.

1:26:23.275 --> 1:26:25.896
Once we turn the carriage ride
into an affair

1:26:25.965 --> 1:26:28.655
for all seasons,
well, I was hoping

1:26:28.724 --> 1:26:31.724
that maybe you would
consider a promotion.

1:26:31.793 --> 1:26:34.344
To partner.

1:26:34.413 --> 1:26:37.172
- [scoffs]
Partner?

1:26:37.241 --> 1:26:41.550
- Well, the lots of little
ideas was kind of your idea.

1:26:41.620 --> 1:26:43.758
- I don't think it's a
good idea for me to stay here.

1:26:43.827 --> 1:26:45.482
What, with our history,

1:26:45.550 --> 1:26:46.931
we shouldn't be
working together,

1:26:47.000 --> 1:26:49.620
even if you are out there.

1:26:49.689 --> 1:26:52.758
- That's a good point.

1:26:52.827 --> 1:26:56.550
What if I were here?

1:26:56.620 --> 1:26:59.448
- Why would you be here?

1:26:59.517 --> 1:27:01.689
- Well,
we're expanding out west

1:27:01.758 --> 1:27:04.413
and as the newly appointed
senior VP,

1:27:04.482 --> 1:27:06.620
I should probably spearhead
that venture.

1:27:06.689 --> 1:27:09.103
Not to mention, I need to find
my boss a new property.

1:27:09.172 --> 1:27:10.344
He's not too thrilled

1:27:10.413 --> 1:27:12.585
about me stealing this one
from his buyers,

1:27:12.655 --> 1:27:14.103
but most importantly,

1:27:14.172 --> 1:27:17.172
I would really like
to take you out on a date.

1:27:17.241 --> 1:27:19.068
A real one this time.

1:27:19.137 --> 1:27:23.241
We can go horseback riding.
A little dancing.

1:27:23.309 --> 1:27:26.550
Wherever you wanna go, I'm in.

1:27:26.620 --> 1:27:28.103
- Good.

1:27:28.172 --> 1:27:31.172
'Cause you still owe me
that projector movie night.

1:27:31.241 --> 1:27:34.034
Just don't screw it up
this time.

1:27:34.103 --> 1:27:36.655
- I won't.

1:27:36.724 --> 1:27:38.827
You got plans tonight?

1:27:50.379 --> 1:27:53.482
